s.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSensitive Privilege Use records events related to use of sensitive privileges, such as \"Act as part of the operating system\" or \"Debug programs\".","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52980","V-26549","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"5263","uuid":"f16bbc2d-fe28-4281-bcb1-f26e80d602ac","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225297","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225297","title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225297","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","rule_id_src":"SV-225297r852191_rule","rule_id":"SV-225297","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000102","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Privilege Use - Sensitive Privilege Use failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration -> System Audit Policies -> Privilege Use -> \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (V-14230) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n-Open a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n-Ente