012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52972","V-26557","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"6310","uuid":"8a1c7142-d45a-43cc-b18d-4a6a480becfe","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 389FBB5E7AFCACA842A554DD277E1299607AF2BB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225305","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225305","title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225305","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","rule_id_src":"SV-225305r852197_rule","rule_id":"SV-225305","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000112","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration -> System Audit Policies -> System -> \"Audit System Integrity\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (V-14230) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n-Open a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n-Enter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following.  If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nSystem -> System Integrity - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52971","V-26558","CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"3572","uuid":"a3d79803-a010-4b71-84e6-bb3c98c8fdda","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F27F4E474A7B5E3D40ED098E8A5E3D5ABFA37C04\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225306","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225306","title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225306","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","rule_id_src":"SV-225306r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225306","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000200","rule_title":"Audit data must be reviewed on a regular basis.","fix_text":"Review audit logs on a predetermined scheduled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine whether audit logs are reviewed on a predetermined schedule.  If audit logs are not reviewed on a regular basis, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To be of value, audit logs from critical systems must be reviewed on a regular basis.  Critical systems should be reviewed on a daily basis to identify security breaches and potential weaknesses in the security structure.  This can be done with the use of monitoring software or other utilities for this purpose.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51561","V-36670","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2281","uuid":"8b1d2bd0-3a58-4c74-a774-71d44f5e74ef","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8F9D5586BBE4DBB33D2AF889F6A22B9C13377C9D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Audit data must be reviewed on a regular basis.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225307","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225307","title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225307","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000255-GPOS-00096","rule_id_src":"SV-225307r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225307","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000201","rule_title":"Audit data must be retained for at least one year.","fix_text":"Ensure the audit data is retained for at least a year.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine whether audit data is retained for at least one year.  If the audit data is not retained for at least a year, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Audit records are essential for investigating system activity after the fact.  Retention periods for audit data are determined based on the sensitivity of the data handled by the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51563","V-36671","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9048","uuid":"a299895d-472f-46af-9680-3964afb93fdc","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 628FBDA1C9B2986049AE2A45B60DCA155EA0CBAF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Audit data must be retained for at least one year.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225308","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225308","title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225308","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","rule_id_src":"SV-225308r877390_rule","rule_id":"SV-225308","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000203-01","rule_title":"Audit records must be backed up onto a different system or media than the system being audited.","fix_text":"Establish and implement a process for backing up log data to another system or media other than the system being audited.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if a process to back up log data to a different system or media than the system being audited has been implemented.  If it has not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protection of log data includes assuring the log data is not accidentally lost or deleted.  Audit information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51566","V-36672","CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"1788","uuid":"0028e36f-d328-4932-9d51-28e1e4a26098","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225309","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225309","title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225309","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","rule_id_src":"SV-225309r877390_rule","rule_id":"SV-225309","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000203-02","rule_title":"The operating system must, at a minimum, off-load audit records of interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.","fix_text":"Configure the operating system to, at a minimum, off-load audit records of interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the operating system, at a minimum, off-loads audit records of interconnected systems in real time and off-loads standalone systems weekly.  If it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protection of log data includes assuring the log data is not accidentally lost or deleted.  Audit information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-72133","V-57719","CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"9267","uuid":"2dd5e8cd-6ad2-495d-aedd-a1bbecac978c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 028C76D802A4540F900C25BC574E5CAFF2A9BAA8\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The operating system must, at a minimum, off-load audit records of interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225310","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225310","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225310","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-225310r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225310","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000204","rule_title":"Permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having greater than Read access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Application event log (Application.evtx).  Standard user accounts or groups must not have greater than Read access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.  They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The Application event log may be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36722","SV-51569","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"5025","uuid":"52295a8f-3fa8-4874-9870-f188e95d5cb8","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5B6005B9293945E8DC84B677BFB9DF3C753F444B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225311","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225311","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225311","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-225311r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225311","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000205","rule_title":"Permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the Security event log (Security.evtx).  Standard user accounts or groups must not have access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.  They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The Security event log may disclose sensitive information or be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51571","V-36723","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"9386","uuid":"eb14a854-e5ac-4e4d-bc3f-6ae82a71b174","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A55FDD7A5BD84374E25E12CE545B67E20B48E15F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225312","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225312","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225312","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-225312r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225312","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000206","rule_title":"Permissions for the System event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","fix_text":"Ensure the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx) are configured to prevent standard user accounts or groups from having greater than Read access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on the System event log (System.evtx).  Standard user accounts or groups must not have greater than Read access.  The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\WINEVT\\LOGS\" directory.  They may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for these files are not as restrictive as the ACLs listed, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  The System event log may be  susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51572","V-36724","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"reference_identifier":"9403","uuid":"d0f6ec72-8f36-47ad-ae8f-cab4fc7148af","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96C071D7A8FF0CA8A2A6AD4B0376449029DACAFF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Permissions for the System event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225313","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225313","title":"SRG-OS-000257-GPOS-00098","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225313","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000257-GPOS-00098","rule_id_src":"SV-225313r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225313","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000213","rule_title":"Event Viewer must be protected from unauthorized modification and deletion.","fix_text":"Ensure only TrustedInstaller has permissions to change or modify Event Viewer (\"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\\Eventvwr.exe).\n\nThe default permissions below satisfy this requirement.\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nAdministrators, SYSTEM, Users, ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & Execute","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the permissions on Event Viewer only allow TrustedInstaller permissions to change or modify.  If any groups or accounts other than TrustedInstaller have Full control or Modify, this is a finding.\n\nNavigate to \"%SystemRoot%\\SYSTEM32\".\nView the permissions on \"Eventvwr.exe\".\n\nThe default permissions below satisfy this requirement.\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nAdministrators, SYSTEM, Users, ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & Execute","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protecting audit information also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit information.\n\nOperating systems providing tools to interface with audit information will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys in order to make access decisions regarding the modification or deletion of audit tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-72135","V-57721","CCI-001494","CCI-001495"],"reference_identifier":"9053","uuid":"11b62811-76b7-47d3-9c12-90bbfadd90fe","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 12565908B4D8067D97DC5287D018AC281EABC87A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Event Viewer must be protected from unauthorized modification and deletion.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225314","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225314","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225314","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225314r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225314","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000001","rule_title":"The Mapper I/O network protocol (LLTDIO) driver must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Link-Layer Topology Discovery -> \"Turn on Mapper I/O (LLTDIO) driver\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LLTD\\\n\nValue Name: AllowLLTDIOOndomain\nValue Name: AllowLLTDIOOnPublicNet\nValue Name: EnableLLTDIO\nValue Name: ProhibitLLTDIOOnPrivateNet\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Mapper I/O network protocol (LLTDIO) driver allows the discovery of the connected network and allows various options to be enabled.  Disabling this helps protect the system from potentially discovering and connecting to unauthorized devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53072","V-15696","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5976","uuid":"6a0d2d12-e699-4f0a-a245-dd537498acea","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 02F351FDEB96A75BF9B929543D8FF770A9CF10B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Mapper I/O network protocol (LLTDIO) driver must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225315","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225315","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225315","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225315r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225315","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000002","rule_title":"The Responder network protocol driver must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Link-Layer Topology Discovery -> \"Turn on Responder (RSPNDR) driver\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LLTD\\\n\nValue Name: AllowRspndrOndomain\nValue Name: AllowRspndrOnPublicNet\nValue Name: EnableRspndr\nValue Name: ProhibitRspndrOnPrivateNet\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Responder network protocol driver allows a computer to be discovered and located on a network.  Disabling this helps protect the system from potentially being discovered and connected to by unauthorized devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15697","SV-53081","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6232","uuid":"e91dae01-5e27-4893-aad6-b09a94aaa4ab","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C606B900C2821CA4F7AF5F6C7D89A01B5F55EC3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Responder network protocol driver must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225316","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225316","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225316","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225316r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225316","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000003","rule_title":"Windows Peer-to-Peer networking services must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Services -> \"Turn off Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Services\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Peernet\\\n\nValue Name: Disabled\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Peer-to-Peer applications can allow unauthorized access to a system and exposure of sensitive data.  This setting will turn off the Microsoft Peer-to-Peer Networking Service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53012","V-15666","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9675","uuid":"dc33d5ac-672b-4bfe-99be-2280494010d1","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E413D49F3C172846CD0D8F3197C595845D695026\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Peer-to-Peer networking services must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225317","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225317","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225317","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225317r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225317","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000004","rule_title":"Network Bridges must be prohibited in Windows.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections -> \"Prohibit installation and configuration of Network Bridge on your DNS domain network\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name: NC_AllowNetBridge_NLA\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A Network Bridge can connect two or more network segments, allowing unauthorized access or exposure of sensitive data.  This setting prevents a Network Bridge from being installed and configured.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15667","SV-53014","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1674","uuid":"d41c56d5-70e6-4fdb-81d1-bca953775369","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 59D07EBA9F7953F6CB5FE13ED846B5BB32DB2F4A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Network Bridges must be prohibited in Windows.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225318","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225318","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225318","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225318r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225318","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000005","rule_title":"Domain users must be required to elevate when setting a networks location.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections -> \"Require domain users to elevate when setting a network's location\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Network Connections\\\n\nValue Name: NC_StdDomainUserSetLocation\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Selecting an incorrect network location may allow greater exposure of a system.  Elevation is required by default on nondomain systems to change network location.  This setting configures elevation to also be required on domain-joined systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-21960","SV-53182","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5813","uuid":"5b487413-5330-444e-be9f-09b326bff1d3","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225319","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225319","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225319","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225319r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225319","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000006","rule_title":"All Direct Access traffic must be routed through the internal network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Network Connections -> \"Route all traffic through the internal network\" to \"Enabled: Enabled State\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\TCPIP\\v6Transition\\\n\nValue Name: Force_Tunneling\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: Enabled","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Routing all Direct Access  traffic through the internal network allows monitoring and prevents split tunneling.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53183","V-21961","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3530","uuid":"99d0838b-75c0-49dc-bd88-e974a781b1ed","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DD786EC7363B5CDB2A168F256417D383D1153B8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'All Direct Access traffic must be routed through the internal network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225324","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225324","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225324","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225324r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225324","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000011","rule_title":"IP stateless autoconfiguration limits state must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> TCPIP Settings -> Parameters -> \"Set IP Stateless Autoconfiguration Limits State\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableIPAutoConfigurationLimits\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"IP stateless autoconfiguration could configure routes that circumvent preferred routes if not limited.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51605","V-36673","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7312","uuid":"f2cfb023-178a-4cab-bd69-52d7167bcc54","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F7B51F99E1FFA95555CAB1A1E2C6F4B07DF04DA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'IP stateless autoconfiguration limits state must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225325","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225325","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225325","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225325r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225325","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000012","rule_title":"The configuration of wireless devices using Windows Connect Now must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Windows Connect Now -> \"Configuration of wireless settings using Windows Connect Now\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WCN\\Registrars\\\n\nValue Name: DisableFlashConfigRegistrar\nValue Name: DisableInBand802DOT11Registrar\nValue Name: DisableUPnPRegistrar\nValue Name: DisableWPDRegistrar\nValue Name: EnableRegistrars\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Connect Now allows the discovery and configuration of devices over wireless.  Wireless devices must be managed.  If a rogue device is connected to a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15698","SV-53085","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1883","uuid":"37a049a1-abd7-4e1c-aec5-894c917756c5","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E912ADEEDF8ED03754D591C1F73144AD5EC8A098\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The configuration of wireless devices using Windows Connect Now must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225326","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225326","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225326","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225326r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225326","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000013","rule_title":"The Windows Connect Now wizards must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Network -> Windows Connect Now -> \"Prohibit access of the Windows Connect Now wizards\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WCN\\UI\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWcnUi\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Connect Now provides wizards for tasks such as \"Set up a wireless router or access point\" and must not be available to users.  Functions such as these may allow unauthorized connections to a system and the potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15699","SV-53089","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7156","uuid":"76d5ca35-b2ed-402d-9b28-f3250c5b3045","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F87CD92EFA05EE4C05D5F9A9ACEBE1380C84DB05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Connect Now wizards must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225327","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225327","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225327","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225327r852200_rule","rule_id":"SV-225327","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000016","rule_title":"Windows Update must be prevented from searching for point and print drivers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Printers -> \"Extend Point and Print connection to search Windows Update\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DoNotInstallCompatibleDriverFromWindowsUpdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting will prevent Windows from searching Windows Update for point and print drivers.  Only the local driver store and server driver cache will be searched.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53184","V-21963","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"3116","uuid":"479026d9-dd78-49b3-9e81-665d377655d4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 91332EEB0A0F0D59FEB27C3E958FA37757C81F12\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Update must be prevented from searching for point and print drivers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225328","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225328","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225328","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225328r852201_rule","rule_id":"SV-225328","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000018","rule_title":"Optional component installation and component repair must be prevented from using Windows Update.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> \"Specify settings for optional component installation and component repair\" to \"Enabled\" and with \"Never attempt to download payload from Windows Update\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Servicing\\\n\nValue Name: UseWindowsUpdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially provide sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Optional component installation or repair must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51606","V-36677","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"7084","uuid":"b82a2baf-7b5a-4afb-8cbb-abd38dbecb7f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E337254B5241782B7B70A2201ACB5792E695EC22\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Optional component installation and component repair must be prevented from using Windows Update.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225329","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225329","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225329","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225329r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225329","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000019","rule_title":"Remote access to the Plug and Play interface must be disabled for device installation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \"Allow remote access to the Plug and Play interface\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceInstall\\Settings\\\n\nValue Name: AllowRemoteRPC\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote access to the Plug and Play interface could potentially allow connections by unauthorized devices.  This setting configures remote access to the Plug and Play interface and must be disabled.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15700","SV-53094","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6883","uuid":"37968dcd-96af-47f9-9043-d0bf997602d5","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":