itives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53099","V-15701","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7840","uuid":"c6e1c97f-3beb-4b83-97d8-e431d3cc66a8","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4EAF7A690B927619584C63BFE6892120D9225C9C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'A system restore point must be created when a new device driver is installed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225332","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225332","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225332","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225332r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225332","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000022","rule_title":"Device metadata retrieval from the Internet must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Installation >> \"Prevent device metadata retrieval from the Internet\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Device Metadata\\\n\nValue Name:  PreventDeviceMetadataFromNetwork\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting will prevent Windows from retrieving device metadata from the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-21964","SV-53185","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3752","uuid":"898a9fcf-d6f2-4c72-a208-2a6c6ac83eb3","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9911699AEBE32ED51F57F52B209D649383CBD76E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Device metadata retrieval from the Internet must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225333","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225333","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225333","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225333r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225333","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000023","rule_title":"Windows must be prevented from sending an error report when a device driver requests additional software during installation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \"Prevent Windows from sending an error report when a device driver requests additional software during installation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceInstall\\Settings\\\n\nValue Name: DisableSendRequestAdditionalSoftwareToWER\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting will prevent Windows from sending an error report to Microsoft when a device driver requests additional software during installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-28504","SV-52962","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4109","uuid":"22950efc-e6b8-44c7-92b2-0d445a276562","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 71C0E6C32A8B3D2508CE7CFD11DEAB2C06899EF4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows must be prevented from sending an error report when a device driver requests additional software during installation.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225334","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225334","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225334","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225334r852202_rule","rule_id":"SV-225334","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000024","rule_title":"Device driver searches using Windows Update must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \"Specify search order for device driver source locations\" to \"Enabled: Do not search Windows Update\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name: SearchOrderConfig\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting will prevent the system from searching Windows Update for device drivers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53186","V-21965","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"7406","uuid":"96eec337-2d9f-4d1c-8a6d-bd24a3bdfcfd","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ECF3F4B919D29FB9F866764EC39DEBEBF1BD65C9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Device driver searches using Windows Update must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225335","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225335","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225335","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225335r852203_rule","rule_id":"SV-225335","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000025","rule_title":"Device driver updates must only search managed servers, not Windows Update.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \"Specify the search server for device driver updates\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Search Managed Server\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name: DriverServerSelection\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially provide sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Device driver updates must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51607","V-36678","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"9617","uuid":"00877a4d-9b2b-4917-af9d-2f00e1d15387","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F83CEC734E7DE9711CEC317C5837D8D9C084745D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Device driver updates must only search managed servers, not Windows Update.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225336","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225336","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225336","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225336r852204_rule","rule_id":"SV-225336","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000026","rule_title":"Users must not be prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Driver Installation -> \"Turn off Windows Update device driver search prompt\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name: DontPromptForWindowsUpdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents users from being prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53115","V-15703","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"4717","uuid":"edee5adf-dcef-4174-addf-dc5ac7f52063","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9828F9F92750606AC1639D0E7C333841CA9BD7CF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Users must not be prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225337","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225337","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225337r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225337","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000027","rule_title":"Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must be enabled and configured to only Good and Unknown.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Early Launch Antimalware -> \"Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Good and Unknown\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to some protection mechanisms that load after initialization.  The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application.  At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51608","V-36679","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5977","uuid":"9af56d45-8c2c-4180-82d1-31405e7a29e6","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F957986E49465F303052058D0EFF83194600EF8D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must be enabled and configured to only Good and Unknown.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225338","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225338","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225338r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225338","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000028","rule_title":"Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy -> \"Configure registry policy processing\" to \"Enabled\" and select the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures that the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed.  This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52933","V-4448","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8583","uuid":"0d28f9a9-6dd8-4363-b137-f1483804a255","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4A46AC241BEBB5F2F8D205BE552D2E8C076218E3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225339","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225339","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225339r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225339","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000029","rule_title":"Group Policies must be refreshed in the background if the user is logged on.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy -> \"Turn off background refresh of Group Policy\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the registry.\nIf the following registry value does not exist, this is not a finding (this is the expected result from configuring the policy as outlined in the Fix section.):\nIf the following registry value exists but is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\system\\\n\nValue Name: DisableBkGndGroupPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this setting is enabled, then Group Policy settings are not refreshed while a user is currently logged on.  This could lead to instances when a user does not have the latest changes to a policy applied and is therefore operating in an insecure context.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52906","V-3469","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3800","uuid":"6e86bcc9-9363-42c3-88c1-921b1ec96b3e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225340","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225340","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225340r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225340","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000030","rule_title":"Access to the Windows Store must be turned off.","fix_text":"If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory exists, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off access to the Store\" to \"Enabled\".   \n\nAlternately, uninstall the \"Desktop Experience\" feature from Windows 2012.  This is located under \"User Interfaces and Infrastructure\" in the \"Add Roles and Features Wizard\".  The \\Windows\\WinStore directory may need to be manually deleted after this.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default. If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoUseStoreOpenWith\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and allow access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  Turning off access to the Windows Store will limit access to publicly available applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51609","V-36680","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1653","uuid":"378a81aa-a03c-4063-b7eb-dc09a577b9ab","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F786B5C3D4CF541E7D8ECC5D621CD02C4BBE5F9E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Access to the Windows Store must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225341","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225341","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225341","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225341r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225341","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000032","rule_title":"Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52998","V-14260","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9750","uuid":"658668d5-9698-47c0-b1e8-090a18e66434","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225342","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225342","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225342","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225342r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225342","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000033","rule_title":"Event Viewer Events.asp links must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off Event Viewer \"Events.asp\" links\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EventViewer\\\n\nValue Name: MicrosoftEventVwrDisableLinks\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Viewing events is a function of administrators, who must not access the internet with privileged accounts.  This setting will disable  Events.asp hyperlinks in Event Viewer to prevent links to the internet from within events.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15672","SV-53017","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1061","uuid":"0573b575-263a-4df7-8dd3-03fae673cbb4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 64D22EAE61F5E555DF3EA3000E64082DFFCF8F82\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Event Viewer Events.asp links must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225343","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225343","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225343","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225343r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225343","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000035","rule_title":"Errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs must not be reported to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off handwriting recognition error reporting\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\HandwritingErrorReports\\\n\nValue Name: PreventHandwritingErrorReports\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs from being reported to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15704","SV-53116","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9364","uuid":"7d33846b-9f9b-495e-9dca-2e7758c240ad","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6D9C940348D05367A54DEBD181393E57D613E60B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs must not be reported to Microsoft.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225344","title":"SRG-OS-000095-