owing registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fAllowUnsolicited\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote assistance allows another user to view or take control of the local session of a user.  Unsolicited remote assistance is help that is offered by the remote user.  This may allow unauthorized parties access to the resources on the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3470","SV-52917","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1177","uuid":"0fffbd5f-0aa7-4f53-8ca1-3d15199d7f64","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 02FBC8FD4CB3469B95AB8D7058E87F5D669A2E14\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent unsolicited remote assistance offers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225354","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225354","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225354","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225354r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225354","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000059","rule_title":"Solicited Remote Assistance must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Remote Assistance -