nticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Remote Procedure Call -> \"Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Authenticated\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name:  RestrictRemoteClients\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring RPC to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server will prevent anonymous connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52988","V-14253","CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"2879","uuid":"aa6d17c5-8d26-43af-b58f-8761c835d38b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 88157AC934ACF5962661E121ED5BE0FA46AF91F1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthenticated RPC clients must be restricted from connecting to the RPC server.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225357","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225357","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225357","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225357r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225357","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000065","rule_title":"The detection of compatibility issues for applications and drivers must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Troubleshooting and Diagnostics -> Application Compatibility Diagnostics -> \"Detect compatibility issues for applications and drivers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePcaUI\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this feature will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36696","SV-51737","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1703","uuid":"0207a3c1-0e20-46d8-9b78-a2645c28728d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1E20784CEC06FAD3D39BC9FE8AE1DE9F3A6BA6C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The detection of compatibility issues for applications and drivers must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225358","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225358","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225358","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225358r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225358","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000066","rule_title":"Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool (MSDT) interactive communication with Microsoft must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Troubleshooting and Diagnostics -> Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool -> \"Microsoft Support Diagnostic Tool: Turn on MSDT interactive communication with support provider\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\ScriptedDiagnosticsProvider\\Policy\\\n\nValue Name: DisableQueryRemoteServer\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents the MSDT from communicating with and sending collected data to Microsoft, the default support provider.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-21967","SV-53187","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4654","uuid":"35c67c30-b5b9-4537-8980-89c576dbc792","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comm