se","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52964","V-26581","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"2865","uuid":"4e05e12e-edcc-4ee0-9228-b27ae66681cc","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AD3BFBBE0603B6CB484146C7BB906DBA9CD0A327\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Setup event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225373","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225373","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-225373r877391_rule","rule_id":"SV-225373","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000087","rule_title":"The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52963","V-26582","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"3546","uuid":"d52647cc-a461-4e64-99df-aad223082376","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225374","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225374","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225374r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225374","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000088","rule_title":"Windows SmartScreen must be enabled on Windows 2012/2012 R2.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with either \"Give user a warning before running downloaded unknown software\" or \"Require approval from an administrator before running downloaded unknown software\" selected.   \n\nMicrosoft has changed this setting several times in the Windows 10 administrative templates, which will affect group policies in a domain if later templates are used.\n\nv1607 of Windows 10 and Windows Server 2016 changed the setting to only Enabled or Disabled without additional selections.  Enabled is effectively \"Give user a warning\u2026\".\n\nv1703 of Windows 10 or later administrative templates changed the policy name to \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\", and the selectable options are \"Warn\" and \"Warn and prevent bypass\". When either of these are applied to a Windows 2012/2012 R2 system, it will configure the registry equivalent of \"Give user a warning\u2026\").","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems; for other systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Give user a warning\u2026)\nOr 0x00000002 (2) (Require approval\u2026)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the Internet that may be malicious. Warning a user before running downloaded unknown software, at minimum, will help prevent potentially malicious programs from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36707","SV-51747","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7469","uuid":"64631004-c6ee-4e62-aa1d-6d03593b6e3e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 96B9E09590EB0E1E23B977AC547902F20F50F2D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows SmartScreen must be enabled on Windows 2012/2012 R2.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225375","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225375","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-225375r852217_rule","rule_id":"SV-225375","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000089","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) provides additional protection by performing  checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running.  This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53125","V-21980","CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2631","uuid":"b4d686ae-ab02-42d5-a8e7-68d8054e4256","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9D3AAE929FA83BF2AB44903D4F0DD2529B3D1F77\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225376","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225376","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225376r852218_rule","rule_id":"SV-225376","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000090","rule_title":"Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt.  Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53137","V-15718","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"6788","uuid":"ef82dacb-8bf5-4f20-a1e7-60212c1d889e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8D0CD2E32CD877A895F6920ECCC20C4B8C2F2E03\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225377","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225377","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225377r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225377","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000091","rule_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will  limit the set of folders applications can open when run in protected mode.  Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53045","V-15683","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7184","uuid":"c34dccf1-8d44-4904-9a82-5bb9856c2944","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4271FA764CB8CB1B07EF690D355139794426170C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225378","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225378","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225378r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225378","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000095","rule_title":"The location feature must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Location and Sensors -> \"Turn off location\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nIf location services are approved by the organization for a device, this must be documented.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LocationAndSensors\\\n\nValue Name: DisableLocation\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1 (Enabled)\n\nIf location services are approved for the system by the organization, this may be set to \"Disabled\" (0).  This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The location service on systems may allow sensitive data to be used by applications on the system.  This should be turned off unless explicitly allowed for approved systems/applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51748","V-36708","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3018","uuid":"bacb6159-b61b-4617-9106-6eecf6cda423","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1AEAACBB2A6BF46A1A219A01845FA073B987BC75\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The location feature must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225379","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225379","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-225379r852219_rule","rule_id":"SV-225379","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000096","rule_title":"Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Connection Client -> \"Do not allow passwords to be saved\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system.  The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52958","V-14247","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"4605","uuid":"158a87c0-1c60-4d24-8e41-2d1cc988fc17","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B1A1AA3C8C516CCF6FCD0BC400666C463A86F5FE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Passwords must not be saved in the Remote Desktop Client.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225380","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225380","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225380r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225380","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000098","rule_title":"Local drives must be prevented from sharing with Remote Desktop Session Hosts.  (Remote Desktop Services Role).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Device and Resource Redirection -> \"Do not allow drive redirection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers to Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52959","V-14249","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5056","uuid":"967485e0-295e-45b4-87bd-9ec52ca742f5","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225381","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225381","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-225381r852220_rule","rule_id":"SV-225381","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000099","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security -> \"Always prompt for password upon connection\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection.  Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52898","V-3453","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"5243","uuid":"cc4fedea-cc00-4bd3-b302-295d95d8919d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 98CF9E863E7838294FA038AAD5AF6962D315B69C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225382","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225382","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-225382r877398_rule","rule_id":"SV-225382","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000100","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security -> \"Set client connection encryption level\" to \"Enabled\" and \"High Level\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3454","SV-52899","CCI-000068","CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"7502","uuid":"a54608f1-01b0-4c03-b066-dc7ad7bb8d6f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 970985AC5074AA10EAD5D47F3FF7FB315CEBCCF9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225383","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225383","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225383r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225383","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000103","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must delete temporary folders when a session is terminated.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders -> \"Do not delete temp folder upon exit\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DeleteTempDirsOnExit\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote desktop session temporary folders must always be deleted after a session is over to prevent hard disk clutter and potential leakage of information.  This setting controls the deletion of the temporary folders when the session is terminated.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52901","V-3456","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9891","uuid":"22a2da7e-7bcf-4a24-b6ee-fec586a43408","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8745B89EC9A07B08419786A244009D58A4D2FA75\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must delete temporary folders when a session is terminated.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225384","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225384","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225384","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225384r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225384","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000104","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders -> \"Do not use temporary folders per session\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: PerSessionTempDir\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a communal temporary folder is used for remote desktop sessions, it might be possible for users to access other users' temporary folders.  If this setting is enabled, only one temporary folder is used for all remote desktop sessions.  Per session temporary folders must be established.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52900","V-3455","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6202","uuid":"38bbe508-6e6e-45e2-9e76-356e1c16db3b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8C484C67202E4A2E128E91330861BE3C55FD9F09\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225385","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225385","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225385r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225385","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000105","rule_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> RSS Feeds -> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure.  This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53040","V-15682","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4569","uuid":"8bc3c80d-853f-4099-bb38-aa2bc81f8155","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DF769101592DFA7F99DC854E64A5B819AF6E3DD8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225386","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225386","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225386","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225386r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225386","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000106","rule_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> RSS Feeds -> \"Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51749","V-36709","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7927","uuid":"9c1f9af2-ca7e-4eb8-93dc-24bfa5eb47b4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FE443034E446670082D00CA9A3A57118260F11AE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225387","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225387","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225387","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225387r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225387","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000109","rule_title":"Automatic download of updates from the Windows Store must be turned off.","fix_text":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nWindows 2012 R2:\nWindows 2012 R2 split the original policy that configures this setting into two separate ones.  Configuring either one to \"Enabled\" will update the registry value as identified in the Check section.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \n\"Turn off Automatic Download of updates on Win8 machines\" or \"Turn off Automatic Download and install of updates\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nWindows 2012:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \"Turn off Automatic Download of updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nWindows 2012 R2:\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\\n\nValue Name:  AutoDownload\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)\n\nWindows 2012:\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\WindowsUpdate\\\n\nValue Name:  AutoDownload\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially allow sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Application updates must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51750","V-36710","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5393","uuid":"50d3d7f4-bd47-4401-b5e8-24bfc8969ffa","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225388","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225388","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225388","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225388r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225388","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000110","rule_title":"The Windows Store application must be turned off.","fix_text":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \"Turn off the Store application\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default. If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\\n\nValue Name:  RemoveWindowsStore\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and provide access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  Turning off access to the Windows Store will limit access to publicly available applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51751","V-36711","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3174","uuid":"0edc68d5-648d-4665-aecb-10fdc4200a8c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D2E192773802C61EAC4E32D14D0BA61047C207E4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Store application must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225389","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225389","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225389","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225389r852222_rule","rule_id":"SV-225389","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000115","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Allow user control over installs\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators.  This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53061","V-15685","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8742","uuid":"e2ae0a42-77be-42a5-bd65-26d0005ef724","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225390","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225390","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225390","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225390r852223_rule","rule_id":"SV-225390","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000116","rule_title":"The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges.  Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52954","V-34974","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8659","uuid":"49f64822-8188-4173-b7a5-5f4e9847e639","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0AC2B2428282551486E461C117FEAB2079B40E8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225391","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225391","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription>