tes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Prohibit non-administrators from applying vendor signed updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: DisableLUAPatching\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  This setting will prevent users from applying vendor-signed updates (though they may be from a trusted source).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53065","V-15686","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5790","uuid":"d6f9544d-de93-49fb-aa13-5da1b09acdee","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 158DCEF9C133405788D0D97A60C91A7A8260E76F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Nonadministrators must be prevented from applying vendor-signed updates.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225393","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225393","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225393","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225393r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225393","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000120","rule_title":"Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) must be prevented from accessing the Internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Digital Rights Management -> \"Prevent Windows Media DRM Internet Access\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WMDRM\\\n\nValue Name: DisableOnline\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis check verifies that Windows Media DRM will be prevented from accessing the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53139","V-15722","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2318","uuid":"8de57cb7-6fb1-4732-9f07-f87648e8d5fe","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 639B961C37EFC2E8BF9E33B2718E1FE463A9BB7B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) must be prevented from accessing the Internet.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225394","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225394","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225394","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225394r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225394","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000121","rule_title":"Users must not be presented with Privacy and Installation options on first use of Windows Media Player.","fix_text":"If Windows Media Player is installed, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> \"Do Not Show First Use Dialog Boxes\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows Media Player is not installed by default.  If it is not installed, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: GroupPrivacyAcceptance\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents users from being presented with Privacy and Installation options on first use of Windows Media Player, which could enable some communication with the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53069","V-15687","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2458","uuid":"6c7e7d3a-338a-46c9-b353-899714379374","stig_uu