G.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access.  Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51757","V-36720","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"7061","uuid":"9d3225e1-c00e-49c5-9ffe-76b98d6a9d34","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 87B93FAC7BEAD3E9FA1EF8833A2BACC3D8191D2A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225402","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225402","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225402","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-225402r877394_rule","rule_id":"SV-225402","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000130","rule_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security -> \"Require secure RPC communication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man-in-the-middle attacks and data disclosure attacks.  A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged.  Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52932","V-4447","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"6908","uuid":"557d83c0-9b2e-4946-b7d6-18ad02cad668","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 21278F73E00B6561ED4618CD982E0B35DE6B054F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225404","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225404","title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225404","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","rule_id_src":"SV-225404r852229_rule","rule_id":"SV-225404","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000132","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from mapping local COM ports and redirecting data from the Remote Desktop Session Host to local COM ports.  (Remote Desktop Services Role).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -