lue on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225408","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225408","title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225408","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","rule_id_src":"SV-225408r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225408","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000136","rule_title":"Only the default client printer must be redirected to the Remote Desktop Session Host.  (Remote Desktop Services Role).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Printer Redirection -> \"Redirect only the default client printer\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: RedirectOnlyDefaultClientPrinter\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing the redirection of only the default client printer to a Remote Desktop session helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52163","V-40204","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1609","uuid":"04a2a842-7adb-48f2-a751-d685895b9734","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66BC4C94499ECD9ADB756141765D31267F3EB450\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Only the default client printer must be redirected to the Remote Desktop Session Host.  (Remote Desktop Services Role).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225409","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225409","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225409","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225409r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225409","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000138","rule_title":"The display of slide shows on the lock screen must be disabled (Windows 2012 R2).","fix_text":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Control Panel -> Personalization -> \"Prevent enabling lock screen slide show\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nVerify the registry value below.  If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-56343","V-43238","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2454","uuid":"d9f7efe8-ccdd-465d-af7d-e870be5d05d3","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 242AB879EA4BB691A07E3E904F27A90E04875889\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The display of slide shows on the lock screen must be disabled (Windows 2012 R2).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225410","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225410","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225410","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-225410r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225410","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000139","rule_title":"Windows 2012 R2 must include command line data in process creation events.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Audit Process Creation >> \"Include command line in process creation events\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012. It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nVerify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00021","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-43239","SV-56344","CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"5426","uuid":"0bacc104-b4c3-4c59-873f-4a32439e6e1f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4780FF935B3F5E5C7CD9C7CBEC303164D2F1092\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 2012 R2 must include command line data in process creation events.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225411","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225411","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225411","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225411r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225411","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000140","rule_title":"The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen (Windows 2012 R2).","fix_text":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Logon -> \"Do not display network selection UI\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nVerify the registry value below.  If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing into Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-56346","V-43240","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6125","uuid":"16827b26-29d0-4714-83f5-edd540ae85dc","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ABC05F49D07B7AF27FC75C9CB5887E38A13D0C92\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen (Windows 2012 R2).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225412","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225412","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225412","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225412r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225412","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000141","rule_title":"The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled (Windows 2012 R2).","fix_text":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> App Runtime -> \"Allow Microsoft accounts to be optional\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nVerify the registry value below.  If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\n\nValue Name: MSAOptional\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of credentials and the system must be maintained within the enterprise.  Enabling this setting allows enterprise credentials to be used with modern style apps that support this, instead of Microsoft accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-56353","V-43241","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3005","uuid":"4ac885e8-5ff3-4f94-9cdf-6980dde4eb2a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BC694A618875DFB35237C5406F6B29FD932FAB3E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The setting to allow Microsoft accounts to be optional for modern style apps must be enabled (Windows 2012 R2).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225413","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225413","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225413","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225413r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225413","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000142","rule_title":"The Windows Explorer Preview pane must be disabled for Windows 2012.","fix_text":"Ensure the following settings are configured for Windows 2012 locally or applied through group policy.\n \nConfigure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Explorer Frame Pane \"Turn off Preview Pane\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nConfigure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Explorer Frame Pane \"Turn on or off details pane\" to \"Enabled\" and \"Configure details pane\" to \"Always hide\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\n\nValue Name: NoPreviewPane\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\n\nValue: 1\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\n\nValue Name: NoReadingPane\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\n\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A known vulnerability in Windows could allow the execution of malicious code by either opening a compromised document or viewing it in the Windows Preview pane.\n\nOrganizations must disable the Windows Preview pane and Windows Detail pane.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-111569","V-102619","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1613","uuid":"8a852211-81ce-4af2-9441-f405f7e04167","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B5663DDC869D9873FD752F1423C0FEBE912A8B8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Explorer Preview pane must be disabled for Windows 2012.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225414","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225414","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225414","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225414r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225414","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000145","rule_title":"Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled (Windows 2012 R2).","fix_text":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Logon Options -> \"Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is NA for the initial release of Windows 2012.  It is applicable to Windows 2012 R2.\n\nVerify the registry value below.  If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows 2012 R2 can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart.  Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-56355","V-43245","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5749","uuid":"8517043f-5ad9-4967-ad59-274ef411f881","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E9ADF9A1B508ABFC08E89A37B286A5955EB11A9B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart must be disabled (Windows 2012 R2).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225415","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225415","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225415","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225415r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225415","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000150","rule_title":"WDigest Authentication must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory update 2871997 is required for this setting to be effective on Windows 2012.  It is not required for Windows 2012 R2.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name: UseLogonCredential\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nNote: Microsoft Security Advisory update 2871997 is required for this setting to be effective on Windows 2012.  It is not required for Windows 2012 R2.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS) exposing them to theft.  This setting will prevent WDigest from storing credentials in memory.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-87391","V-72753","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2018","uuid":"6308e59e-1ad8-46af-96a5-dc8f7026bff2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 909C07D66930EFB722EB45D5C5DB3FAB461A7963\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'WDigest Authentication must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225416","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225416","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225416","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","rule_id_src":"SV-225416r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225416","rule_version":"WN12-FW-000001","rule_title":"A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system.  If a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-55085","V-42420","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2662","uuid":"1eb6e167-42cb-4bac-83c8-4e0e525d3acb","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 130099ED005ECDC317E976B7D2A67F175D4AA80E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225417","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225417","title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225417","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","rule_id_src":"SV-225417r921961_rule","rule_id":"SV-225417","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000001","rule_title":"Systems must be maintained at a supported OS or service pack level.","fix_text":"Update the system to a supported release or operating system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"winver.exe\".\n\nIf the \"About Windows\" displays the following or less, this is a finding:\n\"Microsoft Windows Server \nVersion 6.3 (Build 9600)\"\n \nWindows Server 2012 and 2012 R2 support ended on October 10, 2023.\n\nIf Extended Security Updates (ESUs up to three years) have not been acquired, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Systems at unsupported service packs or releases will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities, which leave them subject to exploitation. Systems must be maintained at a service pack level supported by the vendor with new security updates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53189","V-1073","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3255","uuid":"328022a2-9e72-4786-8a77-57b2f543da86","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A0FDD913181B0E24152C47EAB99951A8FD236241\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Systems must be maintained at a supported OS or service pack level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225418","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225418","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225418","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225418r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225418","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000004-MS","rule_title":"Only administrators responsible for the member server must have Administrator rights on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the system to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system in the local Administrators group.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, replace the Domain Admins group with a domain member server administrator group.\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the local Administrators group. Only the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group. \n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local Administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local Administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nThe built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights.  Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems only using accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group (see V-36433 in the Active Directory Domain STIG).  Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51511","V-1127","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6443","uuid":"dbbac33c-2f36-445a-9989-f7121da6e196","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BCC5FECB1C2E075B03C7D253F6557571714F6A37\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Only administrators responsible for the member server must have Administrator rights on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225419","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225419","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225419","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225419r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225419","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000005","rule_title":"Local volumes must use a format that supports NTFS attributes.","fix_text":"Format local volumes to use NTFS or ReFS.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open \"Computer Management\".\n\nSelect \"Disk Management\" under \"Storage\".\n\nFor each local volume, if the file system does not indicate \"NTFS\", this is a finding.\n\n\"ReFS\" (Resilient File System) is also acceptable and would not be a finding.\n\n\u201cCSV\u201d (Cluster Share Volumes) is also acceptable and would not be a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to system partitions such as the Recovery and EFI System Partition.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The ability to set access permissions and auditing is critical to maintaining the security and proper access controls of a system. To support this, local volumes must be formatted using a file system that supports NTFS attributes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52843","V-1081","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9434","uuid":"7b02ff03-4d22-4830-8577-bad6647b9de1","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 40FEBFA5AD4B2CACAE9102BDDA584FFBC097C72E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Local volumes must use a format that supports NTFS attributes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225420","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225420","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225420","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","rule_id_src":"SV-225420r852234_rule","rule_id":"SV-225420","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000006","rule_title":"Permissions for system drive root directory (usually C:\\) must conform to minimum requirements.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the system drive's root directory and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).\n\nDefault Permissions\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers - Create folders / append data - This folder and subfolders\nUsers - Create files / write data - Subfolders only\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - Subfolders and files only","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).  If the default ACLs are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the system drive's root directory (usually C:\\).  Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than Read & execute permissions except where noted as defaults.  (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\nView the Properties of system drive root directory.\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers - Create folders / append data - This folder and subfolders\nUsers - Create files / write data - Subfolders only\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - Subfolders and files only\n\nAlternately, use Icacls:\n\nOpen a Command prompt (admin).\nEnter icacls followed by the directory:\n\nicacls c:\\\n\nThe following results should be displayed:\n\nc:\\\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(CI)(AD)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(CI)(IO)(WD)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52136","V-40178","CCI-002165"],"reference_identifier":"2366","uuid":"f16036b7-5154-4c9f-b1e3-efb9abd14daf","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 79B4C234A6E3922B41D59741B59FA47867486A75\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Permissions for system drive root directory (usually C:\\) must conform to minimum requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225421","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225421","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225421","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","rule_id_src":"SV-225421r852235_rule","rule_id":"SV-225421","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000007","rule_title":"Permissions for program file directories must conform to minimum requirements.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the program file directories and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).\n\nDefault Permissions:\n\\Program Files and \\Program Files (x86)\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).  If the default ACLs are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the program file directories (Program Files and Program Files (x86)).  Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than Read & execute permissions except where noted as defaults.  (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\nFor each folder, view the Properties.\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nDefault Permissions:\n\\Program Files and \\Program Files (x86)\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\n\nAlternately, use Icacls:\n\nOpen a Command prompt (admin).\nEnter icacls followed by the directory:\n\nicacls \"c:\\program files\"\nicacls \"c:\\program files (x86)\"\n\nThe following results should be displayed as each is entered:\n\nc:\\program files \nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52135","V-40177","CCI-002165"],"reference_identifier":"3196","uuid":"bac7b3b7-f706-4f7d-91fe-629617306d63","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B1B49DD37B9D4A36E232B97F74D5162D5840AC7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Permissions for program file directories must conform to minimum requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225422","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225422","title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225422","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000259-GPOS-00100","rule_id_src":"SV-225422r852236_rule","rule_id":"SV-225422","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000008","rule_title":"Permissions for Windows installation directory must conform to minimum requirements.","fix_text":"Maintain the default file ACLs and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).\n\nDefault Permissions:\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).  If the default ACLs are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the Windows installation directory (usually C:\\Windows).  Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than Read & execute permissions except where noted as defaults.  (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\nView the Properties of the folder.\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nDefault Permissions:\n\\Windows\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read & execute - This folder, subfolders and files\n\nAlternately, use Icacls:\n\nOpen a Command prompt (admin).\nEnter icacls followed by the directory:\n\nicacls c:\\windows\n\nThe following results should be displayed:\n\nc:\\windows\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (V-3377).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52137","V-40179","CCI-001499","CCI-002165"],"reference_identifier":"3636","uuid":"e3afcabc-27f1-4142-98fa-e354d701435e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9A610A9BFF0015651EB76EB646273D1A06DB4EDE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Permissions for Windows installation directory must conform to minimum requirements.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225423","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225423","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225423","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225423r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225423","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000010","rule_title":"The system must not boot into multiple operating systems (dual-boot).","fix_text":"Ensure Windows Server 2012 is the only operating system installed for the system to boot into.  Remove alternate operating systems.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the local system boots directly into Windows.  \n\nOpen Control Panel.\nSelect \"System\".\nSelect the \"Advanced System Settings\" link.\nSelect the \"Advanced\" tab.\nClick the \"Startup and Recovery\" Settings button.  \n\nIf the drop-down list box \"Default operating system:\" shows any operating system other than Windows Server 2012, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing a system to boot into multiple operating systems (dual-booting) may allow security to be circumvented on a secure system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52858","V-1119","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4368","uuid":"00c6c527-56d5-4ca4-bc2e-038591b0c3fa","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D531F9701E833643190BDB72C0AC1AE9C186492\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must not boot into multiple operating systems (dual-boot).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225424","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225424","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225424","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225424r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225424","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000012","rule_title":"Nonadministrative user accounts or groups must only have print permissions on printer shares.","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on shared printers to restrict standard users to  only have Print permissions.  This is typically given through the Everyone group by default.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open \"Devices and Printers\" in Control Panel or through Search.\nIf there are no printers configured, this is NA.(Exclude Microsoft Print to PDF and Microsoft XPS Document Writer, which do not support sharing.)\n\nFor each configured printer:\nRight click on the printer. \nSelect \"Printer Properties\". \nSelect the \"Sharing\" tab. \nView whether \"Share this printer\" is checked. \n\nFor any printers with \"Share this printer\" selected: \nSelect the Security tab. \n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have permissions other than \"Print\", this is a finding.\nStandard users will typically be given \"Print\" permission through the Everyone group.\n\"All APPLICATION PACKAGES\" and \"CREATOR OWNER\" are not considered standard user accounts for this requirement.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows shares are a means by which files, folders, printers, and other resources can be published for network users to access.  Improper configuration can permit access to devices and data beyond a user's need.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-1135","SV-52213","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5660","uuid":"ee1e7d23-66be-4399-a2b2-99a052927749","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A967580AC2481495F15DE99448CD213C0E532764\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Nonadministrative user accounts or groups must only have print permissions on printer shares.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225425","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225425","title":"SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225425","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060","rule_id_src":"SV-225425r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225425","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000014","rule_title":"Outdated or unused accounts must be removed from the system or disabled.","fix_text":"Regularly review accounts to determine if they are still active. Disable or delete any active accounts that have not been used in the last 35 days.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"PowerShell\".\n\nMember servers and standalone systems:\nCopy or enter the lines below to the PowerShell window and enter. (Entering twice may be required. Do not include the quotes at the beginning and end of the query.)\n\n\"([ADSI]('WinNT://{0}' -f $env:COMPUTERNAME)).Children | Where { $_.SchemaClassName -eq 'user' } | ForEach {\n $user = ([ADSI]$_.Path)\n $lastLogin = $user.Properties.LastLogin.Value\n $enabled = ($user.Properties.UserFlags.Value -band 0x2) -ne 0x2\n if ($lastLogin -eq $null) {\n $lastLogin = 'Never'\n }\n Write-Host $user.Name $lastLogin $enabled \n}\"\n\nThis will return a list of local accounts with the account name, last logon, and if the account is enabled (True/False).\nFor example: User1 10/31/2015 5:49:56 AM True\n\nDomain Controllers:\nEnter the following command in PowerShell.\n\"Search-ADAccount -AccountInactive -UsersOnly -TimeSpan 35.00:00:00\"\n\nThis will return accounts that have not been logged on to for 35 days, along with various attributes such as the Enabled status and LastLogonDate.\n\nReview the list of accounts returned by the above queries to determine the finding validity for each account reported.\n\nExclude the following accounts:\nBuilt-in administrator account (Renamed, SID ending in 500)\nBuilt-in guest account (Renamed, Disabled, SID ending in 501)\nApplication accounts\n\nIf any enabled accounts have not been logged on to within the past 35 days, this is a finding.\n\nInactive accounts that have been reviewed and deemed to be required must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Outdated or unused accounts provide penetration points that may go undetected.  Inactive accounts must be deleted if no longer necessary or, if still required, disabled until needed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-1112","SV-52854","CCI-000795"],"reference_identifier":"4940","uuid":"2fd0999e-771b-4258-a160-93e3cd86296a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74AD94BB71B4E3B59C2540EF02802A818527BCCD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Outdated or unused accounts must be removed from the system or disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225426","title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225426","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051","rule_id_src":"SV-225426r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225426","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000015","rule_title":"Windows 2012/2012 R2 accounts must be configured to require passwords.","fix_text":"Configure all enabled accounts to require passwords.\n\nThe password required flag can be set by entering the following on a command line: \"Net user [username] /passwordreq:yes\", substituting [username] with the name of the user account.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the password required status for enabled user accounts.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser -Filter * -Properties PasswordNotRequired | Where PasswordNotRequired -eq True | FT Name, PasswordNotRequired, Enabled\".\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., Guest) and Trusted Domain Objects (TDOs).\n\nIf \"PasswordNotRequired\" is \"True\" for any enabled user account, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone systems:\n\nEnter 'Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Useraccount -Filter \"PasswordRequired=False and LocalAccount=True\" | FT Name, PasswordRequired, Disabled, LocalAccount'.\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., Guest).\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordRequired\" status of \"False\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The lack of password protection enables anyone to gain access to the information system, which opens a backdoor opportunity for intruders to compromise the system as well as other resources.  Accounts on a system must require passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-7002","SV-52940","CCI-000764"],"reference_identifier":"9799","uuid":"5191378b-41ea-4928-846d-03ff57d4dfac","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A450C09D644D8F4B7A82352FCBDCE7A1E27AF8D6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 2012/2012 R2 accounts must be configured to require passwords.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225427","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225427","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","rule_id_src":"SV-225427r857215_rule","rule_id":"SV-225427","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000016","rule_title":"Windows 2012/2012 R2 passwords must be configured to expire.","fix_text":"Configure all enabled user account passwords to expire.\n\nUncheck \"Password never expires\" for all enabled user accounts in Active Directory Users and Computers for domain accounts and Users in Computer Management for member servers and standalone systems. Document any exceptions with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the password never expires status for enabled user accounts.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -PasswordNeverExpires -UsersOnly | Where PasswordNeverExpires -eq True | FT Name, PasswordNeverExpires, Enabled\".\n\nExclude application accounts and disabled accounts (e.g., Guest).\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordNeverExpires\" status of \"True\", this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone systems:\n\nEnter 'Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Useraccount -Filter \"PasswordExpires=False and LocalAccount=True\" | FT Name, PasswordExpires, Disabled, LocalAccount'.\n\nExclude application accounts and disabled accounts (e.g., Guest).\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordExpires\" status of \"False\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Passwords that do not expire or are reused increase the exposure of a password with greater probability of being discovered or cracked.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-6840","SV-52939","CCI-000199"],"reference_identifier":"3291","uuid":"d1a8efae-2bcd-49a0-a0af-8be168e5d75c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 768D57B8032F8AD99B89EEDC5DC8A81C9A172E22\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 2012/2012 R2 passwords must be configured to expire.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225428","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225428","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225428r860012_rule","rule_id":"SV-225428","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000017","rule_title":"System files must be monitored for unauthorized changes.","fix_text":"Monitor system files (e.g., *.exe, *.bat, *.com, *.cmd, and *.dll) on servers for unauthorized changes against a baseline on a weekly basis. This can be done with the use of various monitoring tools.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine whether the site monitors system files (e.g., *.exe, *.bat, *.com, *.cmd, and *.dll) on servers for unauthorized changes against a baseline on a weekly basis.  \n\nIf system files are not monitored for unauthorized changes, this is a finding.\n\nA properly configured McAfee Application Control and Change Control (MACC) module will meet the requirement for file integrity checking.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Monitoring system files for changes against a baseline on a regular basis may help detect the possible introduction of malicious code on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52215","V-2907","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2330","uuid":"bd45e6d1-81c1-4e91-b383-a447c6407689","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 751E802C588D6E71BD48AE8A85F2F68D695272AB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'System files must be monitored for unauthorized changes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225429","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225429","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225429r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225429","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000018","rule_title":"Non system-created file shares on a system must limit access to groups that require it.","fix_text":"If a non-system-created share is required on a system, configure the share and NTFS permissions to limit access to the specific groups or accounts that require it.\n\nRemove any unnecessary non-system-created shares.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If only system-created shares such as \"ADMIN$\", \"C$\", and \"IPC$\" exist on the system, this is NA.\n(System-created shares will display a message that it has been shared for administrative purposes when \"Properties\" is selected.)\n\nRun \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools >> Shared Folders >> Shares.\n\nRight click any non-system-created shares.\nSelect \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Share Permissions\" tab.\n\nIf the file shares have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the NTFS permissions have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Shares on a system provide network access.  To prevent exposing sensitive information, where shares are necessary, permissions must be reconfigured to give the minimum access to those accounts that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52881","V-3245","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7468","uuid":"9094e1ae-29a8-430c-8617-aa3ba5fba780","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 26429CA9F0A08851316EFD56AE1C8DB80C68BCD3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Non system-created file shares on a system must limit access to groups that require it.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225431","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225431","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225431r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225431","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000020","rule_title":"Software certificate installation files must be removed from Windows 2012/2012 R2.","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files (*.p12 and *.pfx) found on a system.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for certificate files, Adobe PreFlight certificate files, or non-certificate installation files with the same extension.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for certificate files or Adobe PreFlight certificate files. Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are not certificate installation files. Removal of non-certificate installation files from systems is not required. These must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53141","V-15823","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5214","uuid":"042006d7-d8fa-4999-a125-33fb6aac8dd8","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8CD97CCFBAD374442A0EC04C2D8B6A330E9BA2A3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Software certificate installation files must be removed from Windows 2012/2012 R2.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225432","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225432","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225432","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225432r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225432","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000021","rule_title":"Necessary services must be documented to maintain a baseline to determine if additional, unnecessary services have been added to a system.","fix_text":"Document the services required for the system to operate.  Remove or disable any services that are not required.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Required services will vary between organizations, and on the role of the individual system.  Organizations will develop their own list of services which will be documented and justified with the ISSO.  The site's list will be provided for any security review.  Services common to multiple systems can be addressed in one document.  Exceptions for individual systems should be identified separately by system.\n\nIndividual services specifically required to be disabled per the STIG are identified in separate requirements.\n\nIf the site has not documented the services required for their system(s), this is a finding.\n\nThe following can be used to view the services on a system:\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nServices for Windows Server 2012 roles are managed automatically, adding those necessary for a particular role.  The following lists the default services for a baseline installation as a reference. This can be used as a basis for documenting the services necessary.\n\nDefault Installation\nName - Startup Type\nApplication Experience - Manual (Trigger Start)\nApplication Identity - Manual (Trigger Start)\nApplication Information - Manual\nApplication Layer Gateway Service - Manual\nApplication Management - Manual\nBackground Intelligent Transfer Service - Automatic (Delayed Start)\nBackground Tasks Infrastructure Service - Automatic\nBase Filtering Engine - Automatic\nCertificate Propagation - Manual\nCNG Key Isolation - Manual (Trigger Start)\nCOM+ Event System - Automatic\nCOM+ System Application - Manual\nComputer Browser - Disabled\nCredential Manager - Manual\nCryptographic Services - Automatic\nDCOM Server Process Launcher - Automatic\nDevice Association Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nDevice Install Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nDevice Setup Manager - Manual (Trigger Start)\nDHCP Client - Automatic\nDiagnostic Policy Service - Automatic (Delayed Start)\nDiagnostic Service Host - Manual\nDiagnostic System Host - Manual\nDistributed Link Tracking Client - Automatic\nDistributed Transaction Coordinator - Automatic (Delayed Start)\nDNS Client - Automatic (Trigger Start)\nEncrypting File System (EFS) - Manual (Trigger Start)\nExtensible Authentication Protocol - Manual\nFunction Discovery Provider Host - Manual\nFunction Discovery Resource Publication - Manual\nGroup Policy Client - Automatic (Trigger Start)\nHealth Key and Certificate Management - Manual\nHuman Interface Device Access - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Data Exchange Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Guest Shutdown Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Heartbeat Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Remote Desktop Virtualization Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Time Synchronization Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nHyper-V Volume Shadow Copy Requestor - Manual (Trigger Start)\nIKE and AuthIP IPsec Keying Modules - Manual (Trigger Start)\nInteractive Services Detection - Manual\nInternet Connection Sharing (ICS) - Disabled\nIP Helper - Automatic\nIPsec Policy Agent - Manual (Trigger Start)\nKDC Proxy Server service (KPS) - Manual\nKtmRm for Distributed Transaction Coordinator - Manual (Trigger Start)\nLink-Layer Topology Discovery Mapper - Manual\nLocal Session Manager - Automatic\nMicrosoft iSCSI Initiator Service - Manual\nMicrosoft Software Shadow Copy Provider - Manual\nMultimedia Class Scheduler - Manual\nNet.Tcp Port Sharing Service - Disabled\nNetlogon - Manual\nNetwork Access Protection Agent - Manual\nNetwork Connections - Manual\nNetwork Connectivity Assistant - Manual (Trigger Start)\nNetwork List Service - Manual\nNetwork Location Awareness - Automatic\nNetwork Store Interface Service - Automatic\nOptimize drives - Manual\nPerformance Counter DLL Host - Manual\nPerformance Logs & Alerts - Manual\nPlug and Play - Manual\nPortable Device Enumerator Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nPower - Automatic\nPrint Spooler - Automatic\nPrinter Extensions and Notifications - Manual\nProblem Reports and Solutions Control Panel Support - Manual\nRemote Access Auto Connection Manager - Manual\nRemote Access Connection Manager - Manual\nRemote Desktop Configuration - Manual\nRemote Desktop Services - Manual\nRemote Desktop Services UserMode Port Redirector - Manual\nRemote Procedure Call (RPC) - Automatic\nRemote Procedure Call (RPC) Locator - Manual\nRemote Registry - Automatic (Trigger Start)\nResultant Set of Policy Provider - Manual\nRouting and Remote Access - Disabled\nRPC Endpoint Mapper - Automatic\nSecondary Logon - Manual\nSecure Socket Tunneling Protocol Service - Manual\nSecurity Accounts Manager - Automatic\nServer - Automatic\nShell Hardware Detection - Automatic\nSmart Card - Disabled\nSmart Card Removal Policy - Manual\nSNMP Trap - Manual\nSoftware Protection - Automatic (Delayed Start, Trigger Start)\nSpecial Administration Console Helper - Manual\nSpot Verifier - Manual (Trigger Start)\nSSDP Discovery - Disabled\nSuperfetch - Manual\nSystem Event Notification Service - Automatic\nTask Scheduler - Automatic\nTCP/IP NetBIOS Helper - Automatic (Trigger Start)\nTelephony - Manual\nThemes - Automatic\nThread Ordering Server - Manual\nUPnP Device Host - Disabled\nUser Access Logging Service - Automatic (Delayed Start)\nUser Profile Service - Automatic\nVirtual Disk - Manual\nVolume Shadow Copy - Manual\nWindows All-User Install Agent - Manual (Trigger Start)\nWindows Audio - Manual\nWindows Audio Endpoint Builder - Manual\nWindows Color System - Manual\nWindows Driver Foundation - User-mode Driver Framework - Manual (Trigger Start)\nWindows Error Reporting Service - Manual (Trigger Start)\nWindows Event Collector - Manual\nWindows Event Log - Automatic\nWindows Firewall - Automatic\nWindows Font Cache Service - Automatic\nWindows Installer - Manual\nWindows Licensing Monitoring Service - Automatic\nWindows Management Instrumentation - Automatic\nWindows Modules Installer - Manual\nWindows Remote Management (WS-Management) - Automatic\nWindows Store Service (WSService) - Manual (Trigger Start)\nWindows Time - Manual (Trigger Start)\nWindows Update - Manual\nWinHTTP Web Proxy Auto-Discovery Service - Manual\nWired AutoConfig - Manual\nWMI Performance Adapter - Manual\nWorkstation - Automatic","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some services may be run under the local System account, which generally has more permissions than required by the service.  Compromising a service could allow an intruder to obtain system permissions and open the system to a variety of attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52218","V-3487","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8798","uuid":"23c58ca5-43af-47f9-87bb-f84e00fb2bf0","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 30284AD7BB3FB591BFFAF31E2300CE18FACFAEA6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Necessary services must be documented to maintain a baseline to determine if additional, unnecessary services have been added to a system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225433","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225433","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225433r793244_rule","rule_id":"SV-225433","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000022","rule_title":"Servers must have a host-based Intrusion Detection System.","fix_text":"Install a host-based Intrusion Detection System on each server.\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: This finding can be downgraded to a CAT III if there is an active HIDS or firewall protecting the network.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine whether there is a host-based Intrusion Detection System on each server. \n\nIf the HIPS component of ESS is installed and active on the host and the Alerts of blocked activity are being logged and monitored, this will meet the requirement of this finding. \n\nA HID device is not required on a system that has the role as the Network Intrusion Device (NID). However, this exception needs to be documented with the site ISSO.\n\nIf a host-based Intrusion Detection System is not installed on the system, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A properly configured host-based Intrusion Detection System provides another level of defense against unauthorized access to critical servers.  With proper configuration and logging enabled, such a system can stop and/or alert for many attempts to gain unauthorized access to resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52105","V-3289","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6042","uuid":"bd0f902a-41cd-4b74-8ed5-358a0336341a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 140720DD716B855DBBA4120E2807527A8765D13F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Servers must have a host-based Intrusion Detection System.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225434","title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225434","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","rule_id_src":"SV-225434r793248_rule","rule_id":"SV-225434","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000023","rule_title":"Windows Server 2012 / 2012 R2 must employ automated mechanisms to determine the state of system components with regard to flaw remediation using the following frequency: continuously, where ESS is used; 30 days, for any additional internal network scans not covered by ESS; and annually, for external scans by Computer Network Defense Service Provider (CNDSP).","fix_text":"Install DoD-approved ESS software and ensure it is operating continuously.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify DoD-approved ESS software is installed and properly operating. Ask the site ISSM for documentation of the ESS software installation and configuration.\n\nIf the ISSM is not able to provide a documented configuration for an installed ESS or if the ESS software is not properly maintained or used, this is a finding.\n\nNote: Example of documentation can be a copy of the site's CCB approved Software Baseline with version of software noted or a memo from the ISSM stating current ESS software and version.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without the use of automated mechanisms to scan for security flaws on a continuous and/or periodic basis, the operating system or other system components may remain vulnerable to the exploits presented by undetected software flaws.  The operating system may have an integrated solution incorporating continuous scanning using ESS and periodic scanning using other tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51582","V-36734","CCI-001233"],"reference_identifier":"4947","uuid":"a65f4446-ccd0-4964-9749-2c2fea0a9be4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1936CF173BAC819E24B3F3249A06EFB3322000B3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2012 / 2012 R2 must employ automated mechanisms to determine the state of system components with regard to flaw remediation using the following frequency: continuously, where ESS is used; 30 days, for any additional internal network scans not covered by ESS; and annually, for external scans by Computer Network Defense Service Provider (CNDSP).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225435","title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225435","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","rule_id_src":"SV-225435r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225435","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000024","rule_title":"The system must support automated patch management tools to facilitate flaw remediation.","fix_text":"Establish a process to automatically install security-related software updates.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the organization has an automated process to install security-related software updates.  If it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The organization (including any contractor to the organization) must promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, hot fixes).  Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36735","SV-51583","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4686","uuid":"b738f47e-0114-4d10-86da-ab6940830673","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7D03D6BC392B87D78E154581050FC865D7B6FA06\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must support automated patch management tools to facilitate flaw remediation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225436","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225436","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-225436r877395_rule","rule_id":"SV-225436","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000025","rule_title":"The system must query the certification authority to determine whether a public key certificate has been revoked before accepting the certificate for authentication purposes.","fix_text":"Install software that  provides certificate validation and revocation checking.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the system has software installed and running that provides certificate validation and revocation checking.  If it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to verify a certificate's revocation status can result in the system accepting a revoked, and therefore unauthorized, certificate.  This could result in the installation of unauthorized software or a connection for rogue networks, depending on the use for which the certificate is intended.   Querying for certificate revocation mitigates the risk that the system will accept an unauthorized certificate.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51584","V-36736","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5732","uuid":"abb36caa-0e0b-4057-8490-626c2f6d4217","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D748AF1C507756153426C90E619904C4A6D296F5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must query the certification authority to determine whether a public key certificate has been revoked before accepting the certificate for authentication purposes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225437","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225437","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225437r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225437","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000026","rule_title":"File Transfer Protocol (FTP) servers must be configured to prevent anonymous logons.","fix_text":"Configure the FTP service to prevent anonymous logons.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nDetermine the IP address and port number assigned to FTP sites from documentation or configuration.\n\nIf Microsoft FTP is used, open \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect \"Sites\" under the server name.\n\nFor any sites that reference FTP, view the Binding information for IP address and port.  The standard port for FTP is 21, however this may be changed.\n\nOpen a \"Command Prompt\".\n\nAttempt to log on as the user \"anonymous\" with the following commands:\n\nNote: Returned results may vary depending on the FTP server software.\n\nC:\\> \"ftp\"\nftp> \"Open IP Address Port\"\n(Substituting [IP Address] and [Port] with the information previously identified.  If no IP Address was listed in the Binding, attempt using \"localhost\".)\n(Connected to IP Address\n220 Microsoft FTP Service)\n\nUser (IP Address): \"anonymous\"\n(331 Anonymous access allowed, send identity (e-mail name) as password.)\n\nPassword: \"password\"\n(230 User logged in.)\nftp>\n\nIf the response indicates that an anonymous FTP login was permitted, this is a finding.\n\nIf accounts with administrator privileges are used to access FTP, this is a CAT I finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories. Allowing anonymous FTP connections makes user auditing difficult.\n\nUsing accounts that have administrator privileges to log on to FTP risks that the userid and password will be captured on the network and give administrator access to an unauthorized user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52106","V-1120","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3443","uuid":"4d932fb7-89c2-4018-873f-85759f40bf8d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 596BB1A43609187733928B06E0887F0B189C474E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'File Transfer Protocol (FTP) servers must be configured to prevent anonymous logons.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225438","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225438","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225438r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225438","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000027","rule_title":"File Transfer Protocol (FTP) servers must be configured to prevent access to the system drive.","fix_text":"Configure the system to only allow FTP access to specific folders containing the data to be available through the service.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nDetermine the IP address and port number assigned to FTP sites from documentation or configuration.\n\nIf Microsoft FTP is used, open \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect \"Sites\" under the server name.\n\nFor any sites that reference FTP, view the Binding information for IP address and port.  The standard port for FTP is 21, however this may be changed.\n\nOpen a \"Command Prompt\".\n\nAccess the FTP site and review accessible directories with the following commands: \n\nNote: Returned results may vary depending on the FTP server software.\n\nC:\\> \"ftp\"\nftp> \"Open IP Address Port\"\n(Substituting [IP Address] and [Port] with the information previously identified.  If no IP Address was listed in the Binding, attempt using \"localhost\".)\n(Connected to IP Address\n220 Microsoft FTP Service)\n\nUser (IP Address): \"FTP User\"\n(Substituting [FTP User] with an account identified that is allowed access.  If it was determined that anonymous access was allowed to the site [see V-1120], also review access using \"anonymous\".)\n (331 Password required)\n\nPassword: \"Password\"\n(Substituting [Password] with password for the account attempting access.)\n(230 User ftpuser logged in.)\n\nftp> \"Dir\"\n\nIf the FTP session indicates access to areas of the system other than the specific folder for FTP data, such as the root of the drive, Program Files or Windows directories, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories.  Access outside of the specific directories of shared data could provide access to system resources and compromise the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52212","V-1121","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4719","uuid":"48dca12b-13c7-4a59-8a6f-4b81a1d0c93f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 60F545B9AC0505B84A4D177C4D0E00CB6E6840FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File Transfer Protocol (FTP) servers must be configured to prevent access to the system drive.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225439","title":"SRG-OS-000002-GPOS-00002","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225439","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000002-GPOS-00002","rule_id_src":"SV-225439r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225439","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000056","rule_title":"Windows 2012 / 2012 R2 must automatically remove or disable temporary user accounts after 72 hours.","fix_text":"Configure temporary user accounts to automatically expire within 72 hours.\n\nDomain account can be configured with an account expiration date, under \"Account\" properties.\n\nLocal accounts can be configured to expire with the command \"Net user [username] /expires:[mm/dd/yyyy]\", where username is the name of the temporary user account.\n\nDelete any temporary user accounts that are no longer necessary.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if temporary user accounts are used and identify any that exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nReview temporary user accounts for expiration dates.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -AccountExpiring -TimeSpan 3:00:00:00 | FT Name, AccountExpirationDate\"\nThis will return any accounts configured to expire within the next 3 days.  (The \"TimeSpan\" value to can be changed to find accounts configured to expire at various times such as 30 for the next month.)\n\nIf any accounts identified as temporary are not listed, this is a finding.\n\nFor any temporary accounts returned by the previous query:\nEnter \"Get-ADUser -Identity [Name] -Property WhenCreated\" to determine when the account was created.\n\nIf the \"WhenCreated\" date and \"AccountExpirationDate\" from the previous query are greater than 3 days apart, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone systems:\n\nEnter \"Net User [username]\", where [username] is the name of the temporary user account.\n\nIf \"Account expires\" has not been defined within 72 hours for any temporary user account, this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"Password last set\" date and \"Account expires\" date are greater than 72 hours apart, this is a finding. (Net User does not provide an account creation date.)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If temporary user accounts remain active when no longer needed or for an excessive period, these accounts may be used to gain unauthorized access. To mitigate this risk, automated termination of all temporary accounts must be set upon account creation.\n\nTemporary accounts are established as part of normal account activation procedures when there is a need for short-term accounts without the demand for immediacy in account activation.\n\nIf temporary accounts are used, the operating system must be configured to automatically terminate these types of accounts after a DoD-defined time period of 72 hours.\n\nTo address access requirements, many operating systems may be integrated with enterprise-level authentication/access mechanisms that meet or exceed access control policy requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-72063","V-57653","CCI-000016"],"reference_identifier":"4452","uuid":"0946bb9c-c1c3-46df-b16e-c7b7a0db1d9c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CC4D4591B3F1340A4A48469B1816F8A0C5580026\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows 2012 / 2012 R2 must automatically remove or disable temporary user accounts after 72 hours.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225440","title":"SRG-OS-000123-GPOS-00064","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225440","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000123-GPOS-00064","rule_id_src":"SV-225440r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225440","rule_version":"WN12-GE-000057","rule_title":"Windows 2012 / 2012 R2 must automatically remove or disable emergency accounts after the crisis is resolved or within 72 hours.","fix_text":"Remove emergency administrator accounts after a crisis has been resolved or configure the accounts to automatically expire within 72 hours.\n\nDomain accounts can be configured with an account expiration date, under \"Account\" properties.\n\nLocal accounts can be configured to expire with the command \"Net user [username] /expires:[mm/dd/yyyy]\", where username is the name of the emergency administrator account.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if emergency administrator accounts are used and identify any that exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nIf emergency administrator accounts cannot be configured with an expiration date due to an ongoing crisis, the accounts must be disabled or removed when the crisis is resolved.\n\nIf emergency administrator accounts have not been configured with an expiration date or have not been disabled or removed following the resolution of a crisis, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -AccountExpiring -TimeSpan 3:00:00:00 | FT Name, AccountExpirationDate\"\nThis will return any accounts configured to expire within the next 3 days.  (The \"TimeSpan\" value to can be changed to find accounts configured to expire at various times such as 30 for the next month.)\n\nIf any accounts identified as emergency administrator accounts are not listed, this is a finding.\n\nFor any emergency administrator accounts returned by the previous query:\nEnter \"Get-ADUser -Identity [Name] -Property WhenCreated\" to determine when the account was created.\n\nIf the \"WhenCreated\" date and \"AccountExpirationDate\" from the previous query are greater than 3 days apart, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone systems:\n\nEnter \"Net User [username]\", where [username] is the name of the emergency administrator accounts.\n\nIf \"Account expires\" has not been defined within 72 hours for any emergency administrator accounts, this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"Password last set\" date and \"Account expires\" date are greater than 72 hours apart, this is a finding. (Net User does not provide an account creation date.)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Emergency administrator accounts are privileged accounts which are established in response to crisis situations where the need for rapid account activation is required. Therefore, emergency account activation may bypass normal account authorization processes. If these accounts are automatically disabled, system maintenance during emergencies may not be possible, thus adversely affecting system availability.\n\nEmergency administrator accounts are different from infrequently used accounts (i.e., local logon accounts used by system administrators when network or normal logon/access is not available). Infrequently used accounts are not subject to automatic termination dates. Emergency accounts are accounts created in response to crisis situations, usually for use by maintenance personnel. The automatic expiration or disabling time period may be extended as needed until the crisis is resolved; however, it must not be extended indefinitely. A permanent account should be established for privileged users who need long-term maintenance accounts.\n\nTo address access requirements, many operating systems can be integrated with enterprise-level authentication/access mechanisms that meet or exceed access control policy requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-57655","SV-72065","CCI-001682"],"reference_identifier":"4839","uuid":"8f0ad061-9745-4075-842d-23f2d2e63afa","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5843D0FBAD8B7E2C029C7F2F2BC6847109039ADF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows 2012 / 2012 R2 must automatically remove or disable emergency accounts after the crisis is resolved or within 72 hours.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225441","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225441","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-225441r922786_rule","rule_id":"SV-225441","rule_version":"WN12-PK-000001","rule_title":"The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates:\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5\nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Root CA certificates are installed as Trusted Root Certification Authorities.\n\nThe certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US \nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF \nNotAfter: 1/24/2053\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates.\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041 \n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint: D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nValid to: Friday, January 24, 2053","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root Certificate Authorities (CAs). The DoD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52961","V-32272","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"1807","uuid":"4349bb60-3f2b-4277-9a2c-9b6e275facb2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7981BADA71AF304679513D03F1C4FD819E973169\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Root CA certificates must be installed in the Trusted Root Store.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225442","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225442","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-225442r894333_rule","rule_id":"SV-225442","rule_version":"WN12-PK-000003","rule_title":"The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed into the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 3 - DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the DoD Interoperability cross-certificates are installed on unclassified systems as Untrusted Certificates.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint : 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 9:57:16 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA\u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued to: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: DoD Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint : 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to:  Wednesday, November 16, 2024","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-32274","SV-52957","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"4604","uuid":"50b912e0-c4c9-48cd-9910-7f79fa4e532c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 419309FB37441C3299714B4591A894380FF3DBD8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed into the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225443","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225443","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-225443r894336_rule","rule_id":"SV-225443","rule_version":"WN12-PK-000004","rule_title":"The US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed into the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\nDoD Root CA 3 - US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 - 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\n\nThe certificates can be installed using the InstallRoot tool. The tool and user guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate is installed on unclassified systems as an Untrusted Certificate.\n\nRun \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025  \n\nAlternately use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\", click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\", click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\", click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA \u2026\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: Subject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025\n\nCertificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52196","V-40237","CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"9338","uuid":"e3597da3-03b1-4478-ae14-8a70e4c72e04","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA62BA1736DBB8E9BD9B07A8854897319A3B81F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed into the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225444","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225444","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225444r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225444","rule_version":"WN12-RG-000001","rule_title":"Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Winlogon registry key.","fix_text":"Maintain permissions at least as restrictive as the defaults listed below for the \"WinLogon\" registry key.  It is recommended to not change the permissions from the defaults.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\nApplies to - This key and subkeys\n\nColumns: Principal - Access\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\nUsers - Read\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry key:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nRight-click on \"WinLogon\" and select \"Permissions\u2026\".\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nIf the permissions are not as restrictive as the defaults listed below, this is a finding.\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\nApplies to - This key and subkeys\n\nColumns: Principal - Access\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\nUsers - Read\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Permissions on the Winlogon registry key must only allow privileged accounts to change registry values.  If standard users have these permissions, there is a potential for programs to run with elevated privileges when a privileged user logs on to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53123","V-26070","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5278","uuid":"72e41f85-943d-48fe-a024-bf534dc2cb7e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D03FFB5E599E1C57932696922F2F9FEC534A3C74\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Winlogon registry key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225445","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225445","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225445r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225445","rule_version":"WN12-RG-000002","rule_title":"Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Active Setup\\Installed Components registry key.","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions of the following registry keys:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\ (64-bit systems only)\n \nUsers - Read\nAdministrators - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control (Subkeys only)\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry keys and review the permissions:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Microsoft\\Active Setup\\Installed Components\\ (64-bit systems)\n\nIf the default permissions listed below have been changed, this is a finding.\n\nUsers - Read\nAdministrators - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control (Subkeys only)\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Permissions on the Active Setup\\Installed Components registry key must only allow privileged accounts to add or change registry values.  If standard user accounts have these permissions, there is a potential for programs to run with elevated privileges when a privileged user logs on to the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52956","V-32282","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2630","uuid":"267c7f4a-7f39-4785-88f9-01d8dbd0e93c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4ECFA2ED8388889AEEA725733C7E576EB396FF39\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Standard user accounts must only have Read permissions to the Active Setup\\Installed Components registry key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225446","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225446","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225446r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225446","rule_version":"WN12-RG-000003-MS","rule_title":"Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> \"Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA. \nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nThis setting may cause issues with some network scanning tools if local administrative accounts are used remotely. Scans should use domain accounts where possible. If a local administrative account must be used, temporarily enabling the privileged token by configuring the registry value to 1 may be required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems.  \n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for local administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36439","SV-51590","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4179","uuid":"cfc0533b-cda3-4108-8456-e36304863a78","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A186555A3FD8EEF684EA0A7B71E938FF5D807A39\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain systems.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225447","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225447","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225447r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225447","rule_version":"WN12-RG-000004","rule_title":"Anonymous access to the registry must be restricted.","fix_text":"Maintain permissions at least as restrictive as the defaults listed below for the \"winreg\" registry key.  It is recommended to not change the permissions from the defaults.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\winreg\\\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - None\n\nColumns: Principal - Access - Applies to\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nBackup Operators - Read - This key only\nLOCAL SERVICE - Read - This key and subkeys","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Run \"Regedit\".\nNavigate to the following registry key:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\winreg\\\n\nIf the key does not exist, this is a finding.\n\nRight-click on \"winreg\" and select \"Permissions\u2026\".\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nIf the permissions are not as restrictive as the defaults listed below, this is a finding.\n\nThe following are the same for each permission listed:\nType - Allow\nInherited from - None\n\nColumns: Principal - Access - Applies to\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nBackup Operators - Read - This key only\nLOCAL SERVICE - Read - This key and subkeys","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require anonymous access to the registry.  This must be limited to properly protect the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52864","V-1152","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1567","uuid":"f7d91a09-76bf-4215-b73e-62cd5ee33da5","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B9947F842ADA1E250B845BC5734DE74F1113133A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous access to the registry must be restricted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225448","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225448","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","rule_id_src":"SV-225448r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225448","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000003","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Accounts: Guest account status\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled.  This account is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted.  This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-1113","SV-52855","CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"6817","uuid":"ba44f3ad-da7f-44f1-ac77-9d0d245febab","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F90CECE65686987116D5149BF52E20091E0A67A8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The built-in guest account must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225449","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225449","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225449r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225449","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000004","rule_title":"Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required.  Password policies should prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system.  However, if a local account with a blank password did exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52886","V-3344","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2415","uuid":"e745aafb-91d4-4363-8e68-d1c1b901597d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 04DCC5070A9B36DD62ADDF02A674937B4D09494C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Local accounts with blank passwords must be restricted to prevent access from the network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225450","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225450","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225450r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225450","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000005","rule_title":"The built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is not set to a value other than \"Administrator\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52857","V-1115","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7504","uuid":"ac4b22a3-50b5-4df4-9a53-23bc4411affe","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E820CD945941EF5649719FD411EEBF019B12EFC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The built-in administrator account must be renamed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225451","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225451","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225451r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225451","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000006","rule_title":"The built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is not set to a value other than \"Guest\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password.  This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users.  Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52856","V-1114","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3169","uuid":"f823cfb4-2ba6-4a47-9e36-277c4f96f78c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B2A37CFA079CCB00A73D8079BE586F786365CAD4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The built-in guest account must be renamed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225452","title":"SRG-OS-000142-GPOS-00071","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225452","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000142-GPOS-00071","rule_id_src":"SV-225452r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225452","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000007","rule_title":"Auditing the Access of Global System Objects must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Audit: Audit the access of global system objects\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: AuditBaseObjects\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\nThis setting prevents the system from setting up a default system access control list for certain system objects, which could create a very large number of security events, filling the security log in Windows and making it difficult to identify actual issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14228","SV-53129","CCI-001095"],"reference_identifier":"9294","uuid":"72628dfb-72ef-4dcf-bce5-a44718629efd","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1917D23B93FA26C3F0E6D4747A20BE22EFA476AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Auditing the Access of Global System Objects must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225453","title":"SRG-OS-000142-GPOS-00071","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225453","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000142-GPOS-00071","rule_id_src":"SV-225453r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225453","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000008","rule_title":"Auditing of Backup and Restore Privileges must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Audit: Audit the use of Backup and Restore privilege\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: FullPrivilegeAuditing\n\nValue Type: REG_BINARY\nValue: 00","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.  \nThis setting prevents the system from generating audit events for every file backed up or restored, which could fill the security log in Windows, making it difficult to identify actual issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52943","V-14229","CCI-001095"],"reference_identifier":"8202","uuid":"981410ed-8aa4-4999-9ccf-45652cb1d474","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C07D1D629B7EF48A38B3CBE9BB21AA13237B36E6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Auditing of Backup and Restore Privileges must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225454","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225454","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-225454r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225454","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000009","rule_title":"Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks.  Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised.  Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.  \nThis setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52944","V-14230","CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"4263","uuid":"368fe739-0c03-434d-acc4-818a21fa5510","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F872A1D06791F39BE97C75A2A306D1712EFC0EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Audit policy using subcategories must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225455","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225455","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225455r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225455","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000011","rule_title":"Ejection of removable NTFS media must be restricted to Administrators.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Devices: Allowed to format and eject removable media\" to \"Administrators\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: AllocateDASD\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Removable hard drives, if they are not properly configured, can be formatted and ejected by users who are not members of the Administrators Group.  Formatting and ejecting removable NTFS media must only be done by administrators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52875","V-1171","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2215","uuid":"8dbea09a-59ce-4023-9288-18730ca1967c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3192844CB2187C3A84C652E0E7873B6423E38262\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Ejection of removable NTFS media must be restricted to Administrators.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225456","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225456","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225456r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225456","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000012","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52934","V-6831","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"3059","uuid":"6aaacfc3-b973-4c03-b687-c670a3f9ebda","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A2C6D1CEB5B54AAE906F2E787BDC0E5B1C25CE08\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted or signed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225457","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225457","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225457r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225457","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000013","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for \"Domain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" is set to \"Enabled\", this can be NA (see V-6831).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52871","V-1163","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5301","uuid":"6532d6d6-8c65-4832-bbb5-383c513372a3","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 525956EDA4FE1A9B361E0776411280567F4E150C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be encrypted when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225458","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225458","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225458r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225458","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000014","rule_title":"Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for \"Domain Member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)\" is set to \"Enabled\", this can be NA (see V-6831).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked.  If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52872","V-1164","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"1932","uuid":"f33dd159-c3b4-4fd6-89f6-b95fbe4d3320","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3F45696C2655F4A6A5BFD69123CC1B405BCA1739\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Outgoing secure channel traffic must be signed when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225459","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225459","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225459r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225459","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000015","rule_title":"The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Domain member: Disable machine account password changes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access.  Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for your system.  A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52873","V-1165","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8074","uuid":"fbb775e1-a2d9-4fa4-be50-a88122a18daa","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CA958E3366E0E7316BA40B90C72B8C1597E17760\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225460","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225460","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225460r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225460","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000016","rule_title":"The maximum age for machine account passwords must be set to requirements.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Domain member: Maximum machine account password age\" to \"30\" or less (excluding \"0\" which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 30 (or less, but not 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis.  This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have.  This setting must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52887","V-3373","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3593","uuid":"89a2abc5-a5d6-425e-b448-74f2f219f40c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F00010B325127C754B844BC4E1854DF4C6F484C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The maximum age for machine account passwords must be set to requirements.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225461","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225461","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225461r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225461","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000017","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nThis setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel.  Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52888","V-3374","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6841","uuid":"03e6fe4a-e3a4-4161-8e5b-05c3ea5ea7b7","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8C190BE09B295AE8650A0434CF82BE9211EF741F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to require a strong session key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225462","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225462","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225462r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225462","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000018","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the display of the last username on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive logon: Do not display last user name\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayLastUserName\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Displaying the username of the last logged on user provides half of the userid/password equation that an unauthorized person would need to gain access.  The username of the last user to log on to a system must not be displayed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52941","V-11806","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4033","uuid":"8215a1ec-2cc5-48c3-a190-4608d7c1ae27","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C54C9DE2874000D7C10AFC27F584EDA2C18A7A39\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent the display of the last username on the logon screen.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225463","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225463","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225463r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225463","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000019","rule_title":"The Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence for logons must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive Logon: Do not require CTRL+ALT+DEL\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableCAD\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling the Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence can compromise system security.  Because only Windows responds to the Ctrl+Alt+Del security sequence, a user can be assured that any passwords entered following that sequence are sent only to Windows.  If the sequence requirement is eliminated, malicious programs can request and receive a user's Windows password.  Disabling this sequence also suppresses a custom logon banner.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52866","V-1154","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5313","uuid":"7c6dffa3-8293-4447-84aa-a4ff1ae8c3df","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 320A4EDCBEF0C41FD471C929518015516C63118F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Ctrl+Alt+Del security attention sequence for logons must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225464","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225464","title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225464","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010","rule_id_src":"SV-225464r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225464","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000021","rule_title":"The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit\" to \"900\" seconds\" or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and should be locked when unattended.  The screen saver should be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected.  This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36773","SV-51596","CCI-000057"],"reference_identifier":"2255","uuid":"03b40506-6c3e-4478-b08d-99b3721dcf4b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 532D7DB72B01613A8C2E91708FAB051CECE21D0A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes, locking the system with the screensaver.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225465","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225465","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-225465r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225465","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000022","rule_title":"The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on\" to the following:\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message text below\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants.  Such communications and work product are private and confidential.  See User Agreement for details.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-1089","SV-52845","CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"1181","uuid":"032ff030-5075-46aa-8981-154145359433","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FD6DABC378E4DD111979BDA2DBBD6393AA676E2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225466","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225466","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-225466r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225466","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000023","rule_title":"The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on\" to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or a site-defined equivalent. \n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in V-1089.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title options below\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or a site-defined equivalent. \n\nIf a site-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in V-1089.\n\nAutomated tools may only search for the titles defined above. If a site-defined title is used, a manual review will be required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26359","SV-53121","CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"6582","uuid":"19efd59e-fe89-4398-b128-5764681ca0e4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9538165E231A8FC967076AA8A4EFE97C1341F5DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225467","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225467","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225467r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225467","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000024","rule_title":"Caching of logon credentials must be limited.","fix_text":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is not available)\" to \"4\" logons or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is not a member of a domain, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  4 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system.  This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable.  Even though the credential cache is well-protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52846","V-1090","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4608","uuid":"36101bd5-0108-403e-8074-4e26ea4a83e5","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6DB9038EFD558415C8C475BDCA86FA37FEDFDFE6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Caching of logon credentials must be limited.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225468","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225468","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225468","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225468r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225468","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000025","rule_title":"Users must be warned in advance of their passwords expiring.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive Logon: Prompt user to change password before expiration\" to \"14\" days or more.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: PasswordExpiryWarning\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 14 (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Creating strong passwords that can be remembered by users requires some thought.  By giving the user advance warning, the user has time to construct a sufficiently strong password.  This setting configures the system to display a warning to users telling them how many days are left before their password expires.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52876","V-1172","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5650","uuid":"30bedb7f-6da0-4bce-b661-bcca5b09428c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F72F805AE8185152A49E776C25501C2C6220DFCA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be warned in advance of their passwords expiring.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225469","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225469","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225469r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225469","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000027","rule_title":"The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to  \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n \nValue Name: SCRemoveOption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nIf configuring this on servers causes issues such as terminating users' remote sessions and the site has a policy in place that any other sessions on the servers such as administrative console logons, are manually locked or logged off when unattended or not in use, this would be acceptable. This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked.  Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52867","V-1157","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1898","uuid":"995e3752-77eb-4a20-87a5-9c04b0e6916c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9272E8D9BF1408B5443D8F5D4208B097C21AA1CE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225470","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225470","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225470r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225470","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000028","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52935","V-6832","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6069","uuid":"f0f7a703-a1b7-4494-9a72-3356329d2a49","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 50B241C2D9FD18EBA1C4CD69E6357287DE97629C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB client must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225471","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225471","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225471","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225471r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225471","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000029","rule_title":"The Windows SMB client must be enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.   If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will request packet signing when communicating with an SMB server that is enabled or required to perform SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52874","V-1166","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5667","uuid":"50a007ec-c09a-458e-820a-dba02567394c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4B66CA186108BD7E651F0C52CA7CF915D1C0221E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB client must be enabled to perform SMB packet signing when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225472","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225472","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","rule_id_src":"SV-225472r877396_rule","rule_id":"SV-225472","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000030","rule_title":"Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft Network Client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain text) password authentication.  Sending plain text passwords across the network, when authenticating to an SMB server, reduces the overall security of the environment.  Check with the vendor of the SMB server to see if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-1141","SV-52861","CCI-000197"],"reference_identifier":"9332","uuid":"0164a882-27b3-4f8c-b6c3-bc1d0ae8a92a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EB71621633FD112F293C1428706440A96FFE74F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party SMB Servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225473","title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225473","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","rule_id_src":"SV-225473r852251_rule","rule_id":"SV-225473","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000031","rule_title":"The amount of idle time required before suspending a session must be properly set.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Microsoft Network Server: Amount of idle time required before suspending session\" to \"15\" minutes or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  autodisconnect\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x0000000f (15) (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Open sessions can increase the avenues of attack on a system.  This setting is used to control when a computer disconnects an inactive SMB session.  If client activity resumes, the session is automatically reestablished.  This protects critical and sensitive network data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52878","V-1174","CCI-001133","CCI-002361"],"reference_identifier":"4175","uuid":"5317bdff-335b-40cb-bb1a-a6e986513a82","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 91C6F7756F784318FD85CCC7CE5042AE983E6630\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The amount of idle time required before suspending a session must be properly set.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225474","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225474","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225474r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225474","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000032","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.  Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will only communicate with an SMB client that performs SMB packet signing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52936","V-6833","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"8502","uuid":"9d9621e3-7b01-4cfc-8cd3-5ebd00623a9d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 85D4DB3102AC234EE722F06CCDE33C4383F6320F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB server must be configured to always perform SMB packet signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225475","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225475","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225475","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-225475r916422_rule","rule_id":"SV-225475","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000033","rule_title":"The Windows SMB server must perform SMB packet signing when possible.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (if client agrees)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations.   Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks.  If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will negotiate SMB packet signing as requested by the client.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52870","V-1162","CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5007","uuid":"4c6cc300-33ee-407b-9395-8b832ab0dc0d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 86CC22DDFEAB4C0AC22BA01C7C5B82B5A3353780\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows SMB server must perform SMB packet signing when possible.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225476","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225476","title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225476","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","rule_id_src":"SV-225476r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225476","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000034","rule_title":"Users must be forcibly disconnected when their logon hours expire.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network server: Disconnect clients when logon hours expire\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableForcedLogoff\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users must not be permitted to remain logged on to the network after they have exceeded their permitted logon hours.  In many cases, this indicates that a user forgot to log off before leaving for the day.  However, it may also indicate that a user is attempting unauthorized access at a time when the system may be less closely monitored.  Forcibly disconnecting users when logon hours expire protects critical and sensitive network data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52860","V-1136","CCI-001133"],"reference_identifier":"2087","uuid":"24228f3b-84c4-4609-9e17-a1f12ffd9e45","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 48E439A8296F5B0E40095B015A14AB3A97FA14C6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be forcibly disconnected when their logon hours expire.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225477","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225477","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225477","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225477r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225477","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000035","rule_title":"The service principal name (SPN) target name validation level must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Microsoft network server: Server SPN target name validation level\" to \"Off\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SmbServerNameHardeningLevel\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a service principle name (SPN) is provided by the client, it is validated against the server's list of SPNs.  Implementation may disrupt file and print sharing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53175","V-21950","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7490","uuid":"046c7fe5-f1c9-4fc8-aff9-1aeb9a66e8f7","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3360EDC4D2FFC6E6A436507DEC4CA4A60ECD7E6E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The service principal name (SPN) target name validation level must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225478","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225478","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225478","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-225478r877377_rule","rule_id":"SV-225478","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000036","rule_title":"Automatic logons must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (AutoAdminLogon) Enable Automatic Logon (not recommended)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nEnsure no passwords are stored in the \"DefaultPassword\" registry value noted below:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: DefaultPassword\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: If the DefaultName or DefaultDomainName in the same registry path contain an administrator account name and the DefaultPassword contains a value, this is a CAT I finding.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: AutoAdminLogon\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing a system to automatically log on when the machine is booted could give access to any unauthorized individual who restarts the computer.  Automatic logon with administrator privileges would give full access to an unauthorized individual.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52107","V-1145","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3532","uuid":"7f61f28a-4e5a-4bc3-a48f-d06bb0302144","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1C70BFB8D279ADAC0B4F6A6C8C7A0F1EF9E78B2B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Automatic logons must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225479","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225479","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225479","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225479r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225479","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000037","rule_title":"IPv6 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53180","V-21955","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9897","uuid":"fa7a4105-484d-44f4-b59e-f02fff201271","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A05542A585B501D15217C9C51CBA3F2CAF777B47\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'IPv6 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225480","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225480","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225480r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225480","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000038","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52924","V-4110","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8621","uuid":"b6d3bd6f-338b-43f4-897d-be10b1fbb106","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 092703F06900A36A0D6F121FBCE72254853DA5FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent IP source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225481","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225481","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225481","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225481r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225481","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000039","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\" to \"Disabled\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly.  When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52925","V-4111","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9312","uuid":"34d12259-05ac-4bb5-9837-8e107282ccc9","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 57C92E13E475D9C5F9EA49F4008721EBAE1C47D5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) generated routes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225482","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225482","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225482","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225482r852254_rule","rule_id":"SV-225482","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000041","rule_title":"The system must be configured to limit how often keep-alive packets are sent.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (KeepAliveTime) How often keep-alive packets are sent in milliseconds\" to \"300000 or 5 minutes (recommended)\" or less.\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: KeepAliveTime\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 300000 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls how often TCP sends a keep-alive packet in attempting to verify that an idle connection is still intact.  A higher value could allow an attacker to cause a denial of service with numerous connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52927","V-4113","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"2207","uuid":"75e7539f-c4ba-4a6a-93d4-959805446b5f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0A64D41BC212696B34AC523DC6D257C9D8FE83AF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The system must be configured to limit how often keep-alive packets are sent.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225483","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225483","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225483","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225483r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225483","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000042","rule_title":"IPSec Exemptions must be limited.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (NoDefaultExempt) Configure IPSec exemptions for various types of network traffic\" to \"Only ISAKMP is exempt (recommended for Windows Server 2003)\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\IPSEC\\\n\nValue Name: NoDefaultExempt\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"IPSec exemption filters allow specific traffic that may be needed by the system  for such things as Kerberos  authentication.  This setting configures Windows for specific IPSec exemptions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52945","V-14232","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7641","uuid":"c1b225b8-00e7-45a9-b35a-0da1235f32fc","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AB658BA6F544A6F1020B33540D751932B226F4F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'IPSec Exemptions must be limited.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225484","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225484","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225484","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225484r852255_rule","rule_id":"SV-225484","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000043","rule_title":"The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers\" to \"Enabled\".   \n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack.  The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the servers WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52928","V-4116","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9779","uuid":"b324be0c-9971-4e38-b813-b8f00270d671","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C6B7C1D9B616E65DCC2A6A9A63D036551581B185\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225485","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225485","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225485","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225485r852256_rule","rule_id":"SV-225485","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000044","rule_title":"The system must be configured to disable the Internet Router Discovery Protocol (IRDP).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (PerformRouterDiscovery) Allow IRDP to detect and configure Default Gateway addresses (could lead to DoS)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: PerformRouterDiscovery\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Internet Router Discovery Protocol (IRDP) is used to detect and configure default gateway addresses on the computer.  If a router is impersonated on a network, traffic could be routed through the compromised system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52926","V-4112","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9114","uuid":"c409cf6b-7046-4f1a-9ca6-15593dce4858","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 57995A7C566E25B50F4C27B05539027A45571103\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to disable the Internet Router Discovery Protocol (IRDP).' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225486","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225486","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225486","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225486r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225486","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000045","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use Safe DLL Search Mode.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (SafeDllSearchMode) Enable Safe DLL search mode (recommended)\" to \"Enabled\".\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: SafeDllSearchMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default search behavior, when an application calls a function in a Dynamic Link Library (DLL), is to search the current directory, followed by the directories contained in the system's path environment variable.  An unauthorized DLL, inserted into an application's working directory, could allow malicious code to be run on the system.  Setting this policy value forces the system to search the %Systemroot% for the DLL before searching the current directory or the rest of the path.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52920","V-3479","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8999","uuid":"b88e0cd8-2de1-436a-8a44-6905862795a9","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7949B3A51DEF5BC73041306584EEDE65B2C7FF32\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to use Safe DLL Search Mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225487","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225487","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225487","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225487r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225487","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000046","rule_title":"The system must be configured to have password protection take effect within a limited time frame when the screen saver becomes active.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (ScreenSaverGracePeriod) The time in seconds before the screen saver grace period expires (0 recommended)\" to \"5\" or less.\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name: ScreenSaverGracePeriod\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 5 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing more than several seconds makes the computer vulnerable to a potential attack from someone walking up to the console to attempt to log on to the system before the lock takes effect.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52930","V-4442","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1297","uuid":"7b3aef25-55e1-4c63-9dc7-50b795342e7b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 27C0837B223E3820C11BB4DC5C95920C0A88CA1F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to have password protection take effect within a limited time frame when the screen saver becomes active.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225488","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225488","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225488","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225488r852257_rule","rule_id":"SV-225488","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000047","rule_title":"IPv6 TCP data retransmissions must be configured to prevent resources from becoming exhausted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions IPv6) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" to \"3\" or less.\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  TcpMaxDataRetransmissions\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring Windows to limit the number of times that IPv6 TCP retransmits unacknowledged data segments before aborting the attempt helps prevent resources from becoming exhausted.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53181","V-21956","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"5968","uuid":"6d1f1c4e-bab2-4f2c-a4aa-43f51dc56a22","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225489","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225489","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225489","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-225489r852258_rule","rule_id":"SV-225489","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000048","rule_title":"The system must limit how many times unacknowledged TCP data is retransmitted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"MSS: (TcpMaxDataRetransmissions) How many times unacknowledged data is retransmitted (3 recommended, 5 is default)\" to \"3\" or less.   \n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  TcpMaxDataRetransmissions\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  3 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In a SYN flood attack, the attacker sends a continuous stream of SYN packets to a server, and the server leaves the half-open connections open until it is overwhelmed and is no longer able to respond to legitimate requests.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52929","V-4438","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"4073","uuid":"7be4eb7b-ef55-4e2d-a68a-59c5bfc3ba40","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 612EF09347D877C53E0E4C4ABD0A40E39ACFE0FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must limit how many times unacknowledged TCP data is retransmitted.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225490","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225490","title":"SRG-OS-000046-GPOS-00022","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225490","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000046-GPOS-00022","rule_id_src":"SV-225490r852259_rule","rule_id":"SV-225490","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000049","rule_title":"The system must generate an audit event when the audit log reaches a percentage of full threshold.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"MSS: (WarningLevel) Percentage threshold for the security event log at which the system will generate a warning\" to \"90\" or less.\n\n(See \"Updating the Windows Security Options File\" in the STIG Overview document if MSS settings are not visible in the system's policy tools.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write to an audit server, or is configured to automatically archive full logs, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: WarningLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 90 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the audit log reaches a given percent full, an audit event is written to the security log.  It is recorded as a successful audit event under the category of System.  This option may be especially useful if the audit logs are set to be cleared manually.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-4108","SV-52923","CCI-000139","CCI-001855","CCI-001858"],"reference_identifier":"3880","uuid":"e66fa193-86d0-49b5-a75d-9b3fcb3fd518","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CB7BCB2878CE879D12CA6BA696ABBAEC15CDC9B0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must generate an audit event when the audit log reaches a percentage of full threshold.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225491","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225491","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225491","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225491r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225491","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000050","rule_title":"Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system.  Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52882","V-3337","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2141","uuid":"5342e83f-81cf-49a4-aae1-35904f95ae44","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 371999A0D78BE13E62100A8DDC187E15705A6F07\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Anonymous SID/Name translation must not be allowed.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225492","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225492","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225492","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225492r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225492","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000051","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous log on users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53122","V-26283","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7229","uuid":"c3d332c2-ba7a-4e3b-bddd-c2e0c9aab1fd","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 39F71AA28E8799C55F7E15D49F926233AA9E7BBC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts must not be allowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225493","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225493","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225493","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225493r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225493","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000052","rule_title":"Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52847","V-1093","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1510","uuid":"6e6be925-eede-4d5b-b55a-5f63d7f31e53","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 23C2153BAEDDF164138882FA97D785887136B3FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Anonymous enumeration of shares must be restricted.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225494","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225494","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225494","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225494r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225494","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000054","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same rights as the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted.  If this setting is enabled, then anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group.  Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52890","V-3377","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9076","uuid":"850c3645-db3c-49ab-affd-b372d68c3039","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225495","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225495","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225495","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225495r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225495","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000055-MS","rule_title":"Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously must be configured to contain no values on member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: NullSessionPipes\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: (blank)\n\nLegitimate applications may add entries to this registry value. If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding.  Documentation must contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously provide the potential for gaining unauthorized system access.  Pipes are internal system communications processes.  They are identified internally by ID numbers that vary between systems.  To make access to these processes easier, these pipes are given names that do not vary between systems.  This setting controls which of these pipes anonymous users may access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3338","SV-51497","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7007","uuid":"53f0b7ab-fc42-42d8-9f97-ba78231036d0","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 072A91070ADA3BED5A7AB7A50A8F5C5E76A28DB0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Named pipes that can be accessed anonymously must be configured to contain no values on member servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225496","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225496","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225496","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225496r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225496","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000056","rule_title":"Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths must not be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths\" with the following entries:\n\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ProductOptions \nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Server Applications \nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\Winreg\\AllowedExactPaths\\\n\nValue Name: Machine\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: see below\n\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ProductOptions \nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Server Applications \nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\n\nLegitimate applications may add entries to this registry value.  If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding. Documentation must contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require remote access to the registry.  This setting controls which registry paths are accessible from a remote computer.  These registry paths must be limited, as they could give unauthorized individuals access to the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52883","V-3339","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"8459","uuid":"7428975c-ce5d-4aae-bda6-9c97f782af42","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77CEA3B38B6CE929E56E3893196F97E2062CF773\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths must not be configured.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225497","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225497","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225497","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225497r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225497","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000057","rule_title":"Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths must not be configured.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths\" with the following entries:\n\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\OLAP Server\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Perflib\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Print\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Windows\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Printers\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\UserConfig\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\DefaultUserConfiguration\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Sysmonlog","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurePipeServers\\Winreg\\AllowedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: Machine\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: see below\n\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\OLAP Server\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Perflib\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Print\nSoftware\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Windows\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Printers\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\UserConfig\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server\\DefaultUserConfiguration\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Eventlog\nSystem\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Sysmonlog\n\nLegitimate applications may add entries to this registry value. If an application requires these entries to function properly and is documented with the ISSO, this would not be a finding.  Documentation must contain supporting information from the vendor's instructions.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system.  Some processes may require remote access to the registry.  This setting controls which registry paths and sub-paths are accessible from a remote computer.  These registry paths must be limited, as they could give unauthorized individuals access to the registry.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-4443","SV-52931","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"3518","uuid":"a73d17e9-465d-4385-9ceb-8cea9137a58a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D755E1884251FC29E11EFE98C1CE48496751213E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Unauthorized remotely accessible registry paths and sub-paths must not be configured.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225498","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225498","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225498","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225498r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225498","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000058","rule_title":"Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous access to named pipes or shares provides the potential for unauthorized system access.  This setting restricts access to those defined in \"Network access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" and \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\",  both of which must be blank under other requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-6834","SV-52937","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"5986","uuid":"1f2aca33-691e-44ee-b857-7a5bdaa4d8e7","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EFEDCB2055455D3C1236A64C9A389CAFB3E66822\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares must be restricted.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225499","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225499","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225499","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225499r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225499","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000059","rule_title":"Network shares that can be accessed anonymously must not be allowed.","fix_text":"Ensure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\" contains no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist, this is not a finding:\n\nIf the following registry value does exist and is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: NullSessionShares\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: (Blank)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous access to network shares provides the potential for gaining unauthorized system access by network users.  This could lead to the exposure or corruption of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3340","SV-52884","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"1763","uuid":"e524ebc9-b4a3-4d1e-bfc0-18af115be991","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F52906CF80857C408F643B12E7A9605FB265247C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Network shares that can be accessed anonymously must not be allowed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225500","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225500","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225500","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-225500r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225500","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000060","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use the Classic security model.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network access: Sharing and security model for local accounts\" to \"Classic - local users authenticate as themselves\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: ForceGuest\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows includes two network-sharing security models - Classic and Guest only.  With the Classic model, local accounts must be password protected; otherwise, anyone can use guest user accounts to access shared system resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3378","SV-52891","CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"9692","uuid":"abc384ed-6f75-4e93-8e9f-1b9384c435e9","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5E0A5856E52ECA3A34ED8CCE753E9E6AE1B648CC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to use the Classic security model.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225501","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225501","title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225501","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000114-GPOS-00059","rule_id_src":"SV-225501r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225501","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000061","rule_title":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity vs. authenticating anonymously.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\\n\nValue Name: UseMachineId\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication may gain unauthorized access if allowed to authenticate anonymously vs. using the computer identity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-21951","SV-53176","CCI-000778"],"reference_identifier":"9260","uuid":"b1702bb2-2c71-46c5-899c-1bd5c05c32c3","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4105906C81F5794F1B3F289D3E913506808B9973\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity vs. authenticating anonymously.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225502","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225502","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225502","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225502r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225502","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000062","rule_title":"NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53177","V-21952","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4370","uuid":"77c0d5e8-a2bb-4ead-b16c-a8730b93e9da","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4AF4939241B27BC4CD17E2B95252C76F18251CE7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'NTLM must be prevented from falling back to a Null session.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225503","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225503","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225503r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225503","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000063","rule_title":"PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol.   This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems.  Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53178","V-21953","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9243","uuid":"14c7f866-6854-4c29-a072-a1a7ce23e2c2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D1DB0E2F56ECA4DAFE005BCD92F32871BD408423\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225504","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225504","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225504","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-225504r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225504","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000064","rule_title":"Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos\" to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types\n\nNote: Removing the previously allowed RC4_HMAC_MD5 encryption suite may have operational impacts and must be thoroughly tested for the environment before changing. This includes but is not limited to parent\\child trusts where RC4 is still enabled; selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" may be required on the domain trusts to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)\n\nNote: Removing the previously allowed RC4_HMAC_MD5 encryption suite may have operational impacts and must be thoroughly tested for the environment before changing. This includes but is not limited to parent\\child trusts where RC4 is still enabled; selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" may be required on the domain trusts to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure. The DES and RC4 encryption suites must not be used for Kerberos encryption.\n\nNote: Removing the previously allowed RC4_HMAC_MD5 encryption suite may have operational impacts and must be thoroughly tested for the environment before changing. This includes but is not limited to parent\\child trusts where RC4 is still enabled; selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" may be required on the domain trusts to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53179","V-21954","CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"5043","uuid":"f0cbd167-7c04-49af-af58-48f1daef2b5d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D1920268151A6B3DFB9269CDBFA899DD284CCC2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225505","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225505","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225505","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","rule_id_src":"SV-225505r877397_rule","rule_id":"SV-225505","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000065","rule_title":"The system must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords.  This setting controls whether or not a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3379","SV-52892","CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"4613","uuid":"feccf1fb-7dad-4756-bd13-188ad7fdd876","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225506","title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225506","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","rule_id_src":"SV-225506r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225506","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000066","rule_title":"The system must be configured to force users to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Force logoff when logon hours expire\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network security: Force logoff when logon hours expire\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Limiting logon hours can help protect data by only allowing access during specified times.  This setting controls whether or not users are forced to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.  If logon hours are set for users, this must be enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3380","SV-52893","CCI-001133"],"reference_identifier":"9130","uuid":"f3a4020c-b0f7-45d0-909f-8b992fbe8e76","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AFB22F5ED208EA0C501767D75D70A11EC943B5F7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to force users to log off when their allowed logon hours expire.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225507","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225507","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225507","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225507r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225507","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000067","rule_title":"The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 5","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts.  NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions  for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it.  It is also used to authenticate logons to stand-alone computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52865","V-1153","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7352","uuid":"f10e4964-5f1b-4ff1-adf9-83fa002b453e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 688A948F008AC037EA25603115890B36E2E86939\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The LanMan authentication level must be set to send NTLMv2 response only, and to refuse LM and NTLM.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225508","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225508","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225508","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225508r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225508","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000068","rule_title":"The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: LDAP client signing requirements\" to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients.  This setting must be set to Negotiate signing or Require signing, depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52894","V-3381","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1832","uuid":"cfe114fb-d10c-43e1-b910-ddfead77d51c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 28378258CEB37DD1352762E8905218F5F648ABDD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to the required LDAP client signing level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225509","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225509","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225509","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225509r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225509","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000069","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP-based clients.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52895","V-3382","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2944","uuid":"0c7a7834-72bd-463a-ba69-d99103fc7827","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8E60FF4BDDE6FB920FEB1070991D8A8719815F83\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP-based clients.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225510","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225510","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225510","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225510r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225510","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000070","rule_title":"The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP-based servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with RPC sessions.  All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52922","V-3666","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2826","uuid":"ceda9832-58ac-4d1e-8754-6108bdf24df8","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D19E96C154958116AA32B2F65D144CD5D32AE16A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP-based servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225511","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225511","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225511","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225511r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225511","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000073","rule_title":"The shutdown option must not be available from the logon dialog box.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Shutdown: Allow system to be shutdown without having to log on\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ShutdownWithoutLogon\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Displaying the shutdown button may allow individuals to shut down a system anonymously.  Only authenticated users should be allowed to shut down the system.  Preventing display of this button in the logon dialog box ensures that individuals who shut down the system are authorized and tracked in the system's Security event log.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52840","V-1075","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9296","uuid":"1f68928f-0c8d-4777-bc05-203b6416a00b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 604B02D720BE779CCE579F3DF90925549C9B36F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The shutdown option must not be available from the logon dialog box.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225512","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225512","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225512","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","rule_id_src":"SV-225512r877380_rule","rule_id":"SV-225512","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000074","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n \nWarning: Clients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms.  Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS, or the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures that the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing.  FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52896","V-3383","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"2200","uuid":"94fea238-a651-4eb9-9d34-2166caa8e589","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D57D4C15AFC3445131C22281550D410659E63AB6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225513","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225513","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225513","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225513r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225513","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000075","rule_title":"The system must be configured to require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"System objects: Require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Kernel\\\n\nValue Name: ObCaseInsensitive\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the behavior of non-Windows subsystems when dealing with the case of arguments or commands.  Case sensitivity could lead to the access of files or commands that must be restricted.  To prevent this from happening, case insensitivity restrictions must be required.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52897","V-3385","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6112","uuid":"7b0ab3fb-b7ea-4752-9a15-29bdd52e2558","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C18D3B9238A37B2A23B054343B1CFFAFE17444B6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must be configured to require case insensitivity for non-Windows subsystems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225514","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225514","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225514","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225514r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225514","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000076","rule_title":"The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic Links)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores.  Each type of object is created with a default DACL that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions.  If this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing nonadministrative users to read shared objects, but not modify shared objects that they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52877","V-1173","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3250","uuid":"f711f82b-2359-477b-a117-68d4a1295360","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1EF90B25B11D46F2AB68C300A6034B3B3242C466\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The default permissions of global system objects must be increased.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225515","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225515","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225515","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-225515r852261_rule","rule_id":"SV-225515","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000077","rule_title":"User Account Control approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00158","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52946","V-14234","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1254","uuid":"984577e7-88fc-4d9b-8a29-6b8ffe739b70","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225516","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225516","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225516","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225516r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225516","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000078","rule_title":"User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Prompt for consent\".\n\nMore secure options for this setting would also be acceptable (e.g., Prompt for credentials, Prompt for consent (or credentials) on the secure desktop).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 4 (Prompt for consent)\n3 (Prompt for credentials)\n2 (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)\n1 (Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14235","SV-52947","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"1769","uuid":"ef4d4deb-69ff-4201-affa-a0ae4515eab8","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56EC71624A5B3B49414FFC32258183494C437204\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'User Account Control must, at minimum, prompt administrators for consent.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225517","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225517","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225517","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-225517r852262_rule","rule_id":"SV-225517","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000079","rule_title":"User Account Control must automatically deny standard user requests for elevation.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users\" to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting controls the behavior of elevation when requested by a standard user account.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00158","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52948","V-14236","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"8321","uuid":"ca65548f-e872-4140-b754-be4ea2e77b85","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EA103B0C75CD33823DDB0E32D86B15EBEDBBA011\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must automatically deny standard user requests for elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225518","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225518","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225518","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225518r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225518","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000080","rule_title":"User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14237","SV-52949","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"8122","uuid":"dbfeedbe-3bf8-4024-8dad-9cae48a61080","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1349A48AB8C9C2D44DB314F142D6EB63EE927A73\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225519","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225519","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225519","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225519r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225519","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000081","rule_title":"Windows must elevate all applications in User Account Control, not just signed ones.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Only elevate executables that are signed and validated\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ValidateAdminCodeSignatures\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\n