,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14239","SV-52950","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"1960","uuid":"4f593f18-e8eb-4610-9e03-0d2007123400","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E96CC6CC5275D8B66B16D4A29F641354F58678ED\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225521","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225521","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225521","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","rule_id_src":"SV-225521r852263_rule","rule_id":"SV-225521","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000083","rule_title":"User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting enables UAC.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00158","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52951","V-14240","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"9028","uuid":"52fae050-df8e-4486-abb2-882f290435dc","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D18B78C8FABD3881FA98DB9F3830AC843534F476\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225522","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225522","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225522","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225522r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225522","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000084","rule_title":"User Account Control must switch to the secure desktop when prompting for elevation.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Switch to the secure desktop when prompting for elevation\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: PromptOnSecureDesktop\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting ensures that the elevation prompt is only used in secure desktop mode.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14241","SV-52952","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6830","uuid":"d0c117a9-3d44-43f0-a9a6-c638e364181f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 877FD1322B99C1C38F4624F11169746422A89E61\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'User Account Control must switch to the secure desktop when prompting for elevation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225523","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225523","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225523","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225523r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225523","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000085","rule_title":"User Account Control must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting configures non-UAC-compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14242","SV-52953","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"7348","uuid":"90f6ad57-0ca3-4af2-99d9-a606ebe6d193","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225524","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225524","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225524","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-225524r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225524","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000086","rule_title":"UIAccess applications must not be allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.","fix_text":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"User Account Control: Allow UIAccess applications to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA on Server Core installations.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUIADesktopToggle\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized.  This setting prevents User Interface Accessibility programs from disabling the secure desktop for elevation prompts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15991","SV-52223","CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3784","uuid":"5537c9ca-3610-4aaf-9ece-9d116c0e0edd","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7B8D76676B549E908B0FA5D4CF6BEB6114077892\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'UIAccess applications must not be allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225525","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225525","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225525","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225525r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225525","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000088","rule_title":"Optional Subsystems must not be permitted to operate on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"System settings: Optional subsystems\" to \"Blank\" (Configured with no entries).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Subsystems\\\n\nValue Name: Optional\n\nValue Type: REG_MULTI_SZ\nValue: (Blank)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The POSIX subsystem is an Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers (IEEE) standard that defines a set of operating system services.  The POSIX Subsystem is required if the server supports applications that use that subsystem.  The subsystem introduces a security risk relating to processes that can potentially persist across logins.  That is, if a user starts a process and then logs out, there is a potential that the next user who logs in to the system could access the previous users process.  This is dangerous because the process started by the first user may retain that users system privileges, and anything the second user does with that process will be performed with the privileges of the first user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-4445","SV-52219","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4723","uuid":"170ecc17-f12d-45ff-8d80-125727ea988d","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BBAB469D72F3575AB48CE0CC9FE880B99DC18A67\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Optional Subsystems must not be permitted to operate on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225526","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225526","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225526","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225526r852264_rule","rule_id":"SV-225526","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000089","rule_title":"The print driver installation privilege must be restricted to administrators.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> Security Options -> \"Devices: Prevent users from installing printer drivers\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Providers\\LanMan Print Services\\Servers\\\n\nValue Name: AddPrinterDrivers\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing users to install drivers can introduce malware or cause the instability of a system.  Print driver installation should be restricted to administrators.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52214","V-1151","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"6935","uuid":"f3f77b7a-0293-44a1-ba93-be18336366f4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8B168096E76239C5CCF5022D81D48110F4DB38B1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The print driver installation privilege must be restricted to administrators.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225527","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225527","title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225527","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035","rule_id_src":"SV-225527r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225527","rule_version":"WN12-SO-000092","rule_title":"Users must be required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Force strong key protection for user keys stored on the computer\" to \"User must enter a password each time they use a key\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\\n\nValue Name:  ForceKeyProtection\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the private key is discovered, an attacker can use the key to authenticate as an authorized user and gain access to the network infrastructure.\n\nThe cornerstone of the PKI is the private key used to encrypt or digitally sign information.\n\nIf the private key is stolen, this will lead to the compromise of the authentication and non-repudiation gained through PKI because the attacker can use the private key to digitally sign documents and pretend to be the authorized user.\n\nBoth the holders of a digital certificate and the issuing authority must protect the computers, storage devices, or whatever they use to keep the private keys.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-57639","SV-72049","CCI-000186"],"reference_identifier":"5844","uuid":"42cdf776-05db-4a63-bbf4-ce7d6f010e3c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B5C5984A3090BD7696FF508BA86ECC22F70BBDF0\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must be required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225528","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225528","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225528","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225528r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225528","rule_version":"WN12-SV-000100","rule_title":"The Fax service must be disabled if installed.","fix_text":"Remove or disable the Fax (fax) service.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the Fax (fax) service is not installed or is disabled.\n\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nIf the following is installed and not disabled, this is a finding:\n\nFax (fax)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26600","SV-52236","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6186","uuid":"57bc9f9d-120c-493d-b5c5-be0a4429c4fe","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E076697BFBE9E86281E35E8821119E90D9DA2853\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Fax service must be disabled if installed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225529","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225529","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225529","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","rule_id_src":"SV-225529r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225529","rule_version":"WN12-SV-000101","rule_title":"The Microsoft FTP service must not be installed unless required.","fix_text":"Remove or disable the \"Microsoft FTP Service\" (Service name: FTPSVC).   \n\nTo remove the \"FTP Server\" role from a system:\nStart \"Server Manager\"\nSelect the server with the \"FTP Server\" role.\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the left pane.\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop down \"TASKS\" list.\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page, click \"Next\".\nDe-select \"FTP Server\" under \"Web Server (IIS).\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the server has the role of an FTP server, this is NA.\n\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nIf the \"Microsoft FTP Service\" (Service name: FTPSVC) is installed and not disabled, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26602","SV-52237","CCI-000382"],"reference_identifier":"5754","uuid":"c7658630-b5aa-4a53-8016-b3b0c9bb262e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3CB39E05E642767598612DB8F5063D6BA2B4CAED\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired confi