nfigured to automatic.","fix_text":"Configure the Startup Type for the Smart Card Removal Policy service to \"Automatic\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the Smart Card Removal Policy service is configured to \"Automatic\". \n\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nIf the Startup Type for Smart Card Removal Policy is not set to Automatic, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The automatic start of the Smart Card Removal Policy service is required to support the smart card removal behavior requirement.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52165","V-40206","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6902","uuid":"7f00bbbb-08bc-4873-9f31-85b1f2e2437e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA6E2115FC1A535B6EF1339D8F41158F515CA040\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Smart Card Removal Policy service must be configured to automatic.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225534","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225534","title":"SRG-OS-000031-GPOS-00012","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225534","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000031-GPOS-00012","rule_id_src":"SV-225534r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225534","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000001","rule_title":"A screen saver must be enabled on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Control Panel -> Personalization -> \"Enable screen saver\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Control Panel\\Desktop\\\n\nValue Name: ScreenSaveActive\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: 1\n\nApplications requiring continuous, real-time screen display (e.g., network management products) require the following and must be documented with the ISSO:\n \n-The logon session does not have administrator rights. \n-The display station (e.g., keyboard, monitor, etc.) is located in a controlled access area.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended.  Enabling a password-protected screen saver to engage after a specified period of time helps protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36656","SV-51758","CCI-000060"],"reference_identifier":"3750","uuid":"a2acd33f-4666-445b-b700-d373891dd7e0","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC430259280377B78F78FA32047F1C7D333823FB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'A screen saver must be enabled on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225535","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225535","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225535","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","rule_id_src":"SV-225535r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225535","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000003","rule_title":"The screen saver must be password protected.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Control Panel -> Personalization -> \"Password protect the screen saver\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Control Panel\\Desktop\\\n\nValue Name: ScreenSaverIsSecure\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended.  Enabling a password-protected screen saver to engage after a specified period of time helps protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51760","V-36657","CCI-000056"],"reference_identifier":"7730","uuid":"6d2541d7-29bd-49c2-aae9-c92531903bac","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225536","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225536","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225536","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225536r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225536","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000005","rule_title":"Notifications from Windows Push Network Service must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Start Menu and Taskbar -> Notifications -> \"Turn off notifications network usage\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoCloudApplicationNotification\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Push Notification Service (WNS) allows third-party vendors to send updates for toasts, tiles, and badges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51762","V-36776","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"2465","uuid":"3ee0eb19-7367-4742-b605-67f4fb3a46e6","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5EA41984BE04089E06C466B1FFA7273DF2C0263D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Notifications from Windows Push Network Service must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225537","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225537","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225537","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225537r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225537","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000006","rule_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Start Menu and Taskbar -> Notifications -> \"Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Toast notifications that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36777","SV-51763","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9000","uuid":"cb0ff540-3150-455b-a018-ce57add50c7f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A73C01C04BCBE349A3B84F36A96BBED23B798710\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225538","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225538","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225538","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225538r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225538","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000007","rule_title":"The Windows Help Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \"Turn off Help Experience Improvement Program\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\\\n\nValue Name: NoImplicitFeedback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting ensures the Windows Help Experience Improvement Program is disabled to prevent information from being passed to the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53144","V-16021","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4728","uuid":"219d073a-d8a2-47fa-a889-10d2b809943b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 08DBCDBD0DAFF38D1CBEB07B174E14385272BD42\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Help Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225539","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225539","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225539","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-225539r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225539","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000008","rule_title":"Windows Help Ratings feedback must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \"Turn off Help Ratings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\\\n\nValue Name: NoExplicitFeedback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting ensures users cannot provide ratings feedback to Microsoft for Help content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-16048","SV-53145","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7168","uuid":"9b89dbf1-3362-4d43-bb23-6dc982e2a5c1","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8A12E5132326E69417D0E2D103066B2F233246E5\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Help Ratings feedback must be turned off.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225540","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225540","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225540","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225540r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225540","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000009","rule_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53002","V-14268","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5178","uuid":"94d99432-7728-47a2-828c-4232480f7aa7","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E78B03457BFB42D9047E3F1F973EB97FB1281CE5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225541","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225541","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225541","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225541r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225541","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000010","rule_title":"Mechanisms for removing zone information from file attachments must be hidden.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Hide mechanisms to remove zone information\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: HideZoneInfoOnProperties\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.  This setting prevents users from manually removing zone information from saved file attachments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53004","V-14269","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1423","uuid":"9bfef965-58a2-46f0-b29a-0b9bb149f6ff","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-225542","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225542","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225542","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-225542r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225542","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000011","rule_title":"The system must notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Notify antivirus programs when opening attachments\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: ScanWithAntiVirus\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attaching malicious files is a known avenue of attack.  This setting configures the system to notify antivirus programs when a user opens a file attachment.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53006","V-14270","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4140","uuid":"09be569a-ba40-485d-b34a-1bc6d890b65a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 67744A81C3D051EDFFCE90BC8BD6BDD64D4C73A5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225543","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225543","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00228","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225543","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00228","rule_id_src":"SV-225543r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225543","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000012","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from sharing files in their profiles.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Network Sharing -> \"Prevent users from sharing files within their profile\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoInPlaceSharing\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing users to share files in their profiles may provide unauthorized access or result in the exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53140","V-15727","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4241","uuid":"fad5c92e-7f5d-4ce8-bf25-be15c018cada","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D17F4F2C4C84A99ACB27217C29276608F44F337\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from sharing files in their profiles.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225544","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225544","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225544","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-225544r852265_rule","rule_id":"SV-225544","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000013","rule_title":"Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic Codec downloads.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> Playback -> \"Prevent Codec Download\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: PreventCodecDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Media Player uses software components, referred to as Codecs, to play back media files.  By default, when an unknown file type is opened with the Media Player, it will search the Internet for the appropriate Codec and automatically download it.  To ensure platform consistency and to protect against new vulnerabilities associated with media types, all Codecs must be installed by the System Administrator.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52921","V-3481","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"9870","uuid":"b1e8822c-cba0-4f9c-ab4e-4e4fbf84f8a2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 81FDC80CCDF5166E51517384DEFA973B8D8BE637\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic Codec downloads.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225545","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225545","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225545","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225545r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225545","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000001","rule_title":"The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53120","V-26469","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2055","uuid":"6bd5ccb8-c19a-4edc-a5fd-be2b9f3030a2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9ADA81F313BEF2CB306678C7C0C4BA6236027244\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225546","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225546","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225546","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225546r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225546","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000002-MS","rule_title":"The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Authenticated Users groups on member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nAuthenticated Users","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nAuthenticated Users\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (V-36661) and required changes frequency (V-36662).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and must be limited to those that require it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51499","V-26470","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5765","uuid":"c257a73f-4707-490f-9357-9ed6c2ba5e8a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7F30A7A00205C5974BBCF59104254EFFDC9D5A99\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Authenticated Users groups on member servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225547","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225547","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225547","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225547r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225547","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000003","rule_title":"The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access.  Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52108","V-1102","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6635","uuid":"14dc5c15-0783-4892-9d04-e32ae541f69a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 62DC731A57DA8AECF636D13A5054208E44CD980F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225548","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225548","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225548","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225548r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225548","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000005","rule_title":"The Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on locally\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52110","V-26472","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5250","uuid":"b1328e9f-0a92-4b6a-bd4d-cce672f69c48","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F8022DD18657392839E5D43FC8CD93847B22D169\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225549","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225549","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225549","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225549r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225549","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000006-MS","rule_title":"The Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group and other approved groups.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators   \n\nIf the system serves the Remote Desktop Services role, the Remote Desktop Users group or another more restrictive group may be included.  \n\nOrganizations may grant this to other groups, such as more restrictive groups with administrative or management functions, if required.  Remote Desktop Services access must be restricted to the accounts that require it.  This must be documented with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the system serves the Remote Desktop Services role, the Remote Desktop Users group or another more restrictive group may be included.  \n\nOrganizations may grant this to other groups, such as more restrictive groups with administrative or management functions, if required.  Remote Desktop Services access must be restricted to the accounts that require it.  This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right can access a system through Remote Desktop.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-83319","V-26473","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2374","uuid":"33f1a184-8ff9-46c8-8dc9-bb662bdb0a4a","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 464F87EB6198A730154379B0BBFFD5E6401CFDA7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group and other approved groups.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225550","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225550","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225550","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225550r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225550","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000007","rule_title":"The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Back up files and directories\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52111","V-26474","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8686","uuid":"ea9ecc0d-c064-4874-94a4-7ce9ca0c668c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FDDEF3233DD650812F0A957E89C2E2999A80D89F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225551","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225551","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225551","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225551r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225551","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000011","rule_title":"The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a pagefile\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53063","V-26478","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5438","uuid":"e106425a-94ab-4b20-a4a4-f63e360d234b","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3F564E8C89BF1C0B500B1C48A0EAD39147706D7E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225552","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225552","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225552","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225552r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225552","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000012","rule_title":"The Create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a token object\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52113","V-26479","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5586","uuid":"dda6c0b1-a60e-4f3a-b26e-7c7c0053892c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FD003A27C2F3E3E6121C87842FC91C40E05C8E09\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225553","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225553","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225553","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225553r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225553","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000013","rule_title":"The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create global objects\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52114","V-26480","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2740","uuid":"aa35d738-15b5-4256-9080-a0712290ac09","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F50AC9685B88DCFF3262537E1750FD54B7A95E37\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225554","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225554","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225554","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225554r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225554","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000014","rule_title":"The Create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create permanent shared objects\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53059","V-26481","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2052","uuid":"3cfcd8dc-3ce0-4ecf-a23d-7da7f23c8e62","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 245F3A14250DFCF0B7AEB9872D905A38D373E67A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225555","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225555","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225555","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225555r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225555","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000015","rule_title":"The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create symbolic links\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right.  If this needs to be added manually, enter it as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right (this may be displayed as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\").  This is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could potentially expose the system to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53054","V-26482","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1938","uuid":"8fa291d7-54b5-44d6-89f0-bfe2bc2f2657","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2DB45A2BE827877E0607BC5D70E707E5434E836F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225556","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225556","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225556","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225556r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225556","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000016","rule_title":"The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Debug programs\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Debug programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components.  This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52115","V-18010","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3914","uuid":"05a8fbc0-8df5-49ee-86d4-51d0f74c4b30","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D1AA53FE8BF249354A8E906CA92305FE4B037AAA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225557","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225557","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225557","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225557r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225557","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000017-MS","rule_title":"The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\n\"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nNote: Windows Server 2012 R2 added new built-in security groups, \"Local account\" and \"Local account and member of Administrators group\". \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide Failover Clustering.\nMicrosoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds the new security groups to Windows Server 2012.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\n\"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nNote: Windows Server 2012 R2 added new built-in security groups, \"Local account\" and \"Local account and member of Administrators group\". \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide Failover Clustering.\nMicrosoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds the new security groups to Windows Server 2012.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51501","V-1155","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9609","uuid":"3bccacf1-9766-4207-a4bd-d0b3d7920b02","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E50402E6E358B6D6CBB4982E74842A298753EC6A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225558","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225558","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225558","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225558r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225558","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000018-MS","rule_title":"The Deny log on as a batch job user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on as a batch job\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job such, as Task Scheduler.  \n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26483","SV-51502","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8274","uuid":"640307d5-4a53-4ec6-9deb-2028015c39bf","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A5F194C524F00A577656634049F2C383EAECB9E2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Deny log on as a batch job user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225559","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225559","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225559","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225559r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225559","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000019-MS","rule_title":"The Deny log on as a service user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems.  No other groups or accounts must be assigned this right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on as a service\" to include the following for domain-joined systems:\n\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nConfigure the \"Deny log on as a service\" for nondomain systems to include no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on domain-joined systems, this is a finding:\n\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on non-domain-joined systems, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied log on as a service.  \n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51504","V-26484","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6254","uuid":"1cb200d2-f8a3-4564-836a-2f372274027c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 80CDBFEA48E3BEA110EDD00C7D228D7E4045BB43\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Deny log on as a service user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems.  No other groups or accounts must be assigned this right.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225560","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225560","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225560","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225560r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225560","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000020-MS","rule_title":"The Deny log on locally user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on locally\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins Group\nDomain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.  \n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51508","V-26485","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1818","uuid":"ec7f4ffc-fedd-42d6-9c46-be0b26fd54d2","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9DAAC47CED3716A856B4BE30D4BBBB6814D6DAB2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on locally user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225561","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225561","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225561","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-225561r569185_rule","rule_id":"SV-225561","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000021-MS","rule_title":"The Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nNote: Windows Server 2012 R2 added new built-in security groups, including \"Local account\", for assigning permissions and rights to all local accounts. \nMicrosoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds the new security groups to Windows Server 2012.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nEnterprise Admins group\nDomain Admins group\nLocal account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\nGuests group\n\nNote: Windows Server 2012 R2 added new built-in security groups, including \"Local account\", for assigning permissions and rights to all local accounts. \nMicrosoft Security Advisory Patch 2871997 adds the new security groups to Windows Server 2012.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51509","V-26486","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6273","uuid":"e6121130-bbba-4be4-a17b-464bd0e6a0b4","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8EDB8909DE37CC9A7ED283AFDDE7D7EEF83E337B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts on domain systems, and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225562","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225562","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225562","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225562r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225562","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000022-MS","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right on member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed.  This could potentially allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51500","V-26487","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6154","uuid":"10a6f125-4a7c-4046-9a48-c76f87428cf9","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A6E9EDADA05896076123CDC971791DE629AD650C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right on member servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225563","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225563","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225563","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225563r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225563","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000023","rule_title":"The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system, which could result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53050","V-26488","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9031","uuid":"77352760-81b9-43cb-b975-911c3f722767","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9E91A1F6DDF4E90DEC01666D45E6F399817B9B73\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225564","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225564","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225564","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225564r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225564","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000024","rule_title":"The Generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Generate security audits\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Generate security audits\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Generate security audits\" user right specifies users and processes that can generate Security Log audit records, which must only be the system service accounts defined.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52116","V-26489","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3777","uuid":"80390a0a-5824-481c-8d6d-058f656f708c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1BF1057CC6CFD32A57E1D1D8A805A7376AD92235\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225565","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225565","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225565","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225565r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225565","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000025","rule_title":"The Impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf.  An attacker could potentially use this to elevate privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52117","V-26490","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4768","uuid":"bf3ad8b3-892e-4e3b-9e54-a101aaa45870","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A15B725CFA06551A968F7D408877E8E1523EB9E6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225566","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225566","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225566","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225566r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225566","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000027","rule_title":"The Increase scheduling priority user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Increase scheduling priority\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right can change a scheduling priority causing performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52118","V-26492","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2717","uuid":"5cdc1451-ad74-4c76-a584-9efb68006a7e","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1D5AC2DC0C8C3D7B0FBDA66C41683B87EEEAF620\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Increase scheduling priority user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225567","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225567","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225567","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225567r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225567","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000028","rule_title":"The Load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Load and unload device drivers\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right allows device drivers to dynamically be loaded on a system by a user.  This could potentially be used to install malicious code by an attacker.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53043","V-26493","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2200","uuid":"e6c486a8-ee15-49ae-bece-a3082b61b10c","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5C1ED7AA32AAA741C9AC93FCAED74F8A252B5974\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225568","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225568","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225568","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-225568r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-225568","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000029","rule_title":"The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Lock pages in memory\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52119","V-26494","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4863","uuid":"aede20f6-1c02-4b67-8920-8a06488f3c15","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4F8BB6101936E267CE8B3802E2801ABD0539EC4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225569","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225569","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225569","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-225569r852282_rule","rule_id":"SV-225569","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000032","rule_title":"The Manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Manage auditing and security log\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the organization has an Auditors group, the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required 