 values\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_MS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right can change hardware configuration environment variables.  This could result in hardware failures or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53029","V-26498","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3386","uuid":"4cbe7180-b8a2-4bed-85be-58e6d7273d6f","stig_uuid":"c86c759d-312b-4407-8dff-54b4acc214e1","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2MS_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ECDAB9AA5AC1AAB2D901296B24DE34427CECE932\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-225571","group_tree":[{"id":"V-225571","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-225571","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_